column13: Best sun protection you'll get for the price, & for sweat and water resistance, too.
column14: I'm a redhead living in Chicago and I play soccer every Sunday and run during week days, and this keeps me pale and sunburn free better than any other product out there. I know their products aren't rated well when you look at chemicals used and and all that, but nothing at this price point will protect me better from sunburn on a blazing hot August afternoon.  I reapply at halftime during games, because no matter how sweat proof it claims to be, I wipe my face clean over and over, and that will remove the sunscreen over time.  I also rarely have issues with this burning my eyes, which are very sensitive.  I always apply the first time about 30 minutes before sun exposure, to let it soak in, and that will help keep it from running into your eyes. When I reapply at halftime, sometimes it gets a little in my eyes, but that's because I'm already sweating, nothing you can do about that!! But their is no better alternative at this price point.  I've also never broken out or had any skin issues that I could relate to using this product.

column14:
I have used the old style Norelco for many years and think this new cleaning tank is an expensive waste!! Here is what I do and it will work for any Norelco shaver. I have a small plastic upper ware cup which I pour approximately 1/2 inch of 70 or 90% proof alcohol which can be purchased at your drug store for around $3.00 or less for a good size bottle. Once a week I run the shaver with the head into the alcohol for 20 or 30 seconds. Then open the head and run water thru it and you have a bright clean sterile shaving head. Try it and you will see that it works. Been doing it for years!!
Dave Garber

column14: This stuff works! I just mixed it with witch hazel and I have been spraying it on at night when I sit outside. So far I am not mosquito bait. I am a person who always gets bit. I bought this to use in Nicaragua and accidentally left the bottle in the refrigerator. I got eaten alive day and night in Belize. When I got back to the states I bought it again for our travels. I have been using here in Dominican Republic with great success. We go on to Panama and then Mexico so I am hopeful I will have the same results. Also I started taking B1, although some research suggests that doesn't work. I have also read to eat garlic. So there are orders the Mosquitos don't like. The insect shield is not offensive to me and way better than spraying deet on your body. I recommend trying and I hope it works for you! Ok it did not work on the biting midges or no see us in Boca Chica Panama but it works great on the mosquitos in Mexico. Also you can dot a few drops on your skin on pulse points like you do perfume. I have seen mosquitos come close to my leg to land and about 3 to 4 inches away they turn and fly away. Remember to carry a spray bottle and spray under the table on your legs when out at night. This is great because it is a natural product.

column6: Best Face Cream for Wrinkles and Anti Aging - Daily Moisturizer with Matrixyl + Argireline + Hyaluronic Acid + Vitamin C + Vitamin E for Wrinkle Repair - Must Have Day Cream for Fine Lines
column13: From unknown to my favorite in days!
column14:
I am 23 and although I don't have many wrinkles or expression lines I do have some and want to make sure I look young as long as possible. I know I sound shallow but let's be real, we all hope to stay young long. I didn't think to take a before picture because I really didn't think that this would work but I do have a picture where you can see my wrinkles a tad if you look in the white circle closely you can see them. I have been using this face Creme for a week and saw results after one day! The texture of the Creme is thick but it isn't greasy. The smell hits you as soon as you open it. It smells like big red on someone's breathe sweet but spicy. I actually double took my face the morning after the first night of use. I woke up and my expression lines were visibly relaxed from the Argireline just as it claims! Throughout the week I have noticed that my wrinkle lines are becoming less visible. My skin does look younger! The reason I am giving this a 4 instead of a 5 is because for about 10 minutes after I put this on my skin is red and blotchy. I am assuming that is due to the plumping effect because it does go away but at the time it worries me. I actually think that my skin is better then it's been in a while even though I just started using this. I loved this so much I went back and requested to try the eye creme.

I was sent this product for review purposes but my review is 100% my own opinion!

column13: For a guy, it works ....... kind of, read.....
column14: For a guy in his early 40, this face cream works [update: this review is NOT for the Olay Miracle Boost] .......... well, kind of. I have been using Olay's Regenerist Micro Sculpting creme for several years (off and on) and have always liked how WELL it hydrates my face [my main reason for using it] and that lovely soft dewy look it gives my skin. The product works well for about two weeks then starts to go south due to it being in a jar, rather than being in tube that is air sealed. It STILL works at hydrating but not so great at that dewy look due to air degrading the ingredients. A tube packaging it not at flashy chic looking but very sound at keeping the product fresh. However, I do like the blend of ingredients and how it feels on my skin without that greasy wet oily sticky feel of some other brands that charge 'an arm and a leg' for a jar.

I love pedi-cures and I love doing them at home. This remover is so much better then the other ones on the market as you have to constantly buy and change the batteries. Well not anymore this one comes with a rechargeable battery for your convenience.

AUTOMATIC, PORTABLE, & CONVENIENT - No need to waste so many batteries, this unit holds a rechargeable battery and comes with an AC adapter. Lightweight, ergonomic, and handy, you can put it in its storage pouch and take with you when traveling.

column13: Another great product from Andalou Naturals
column14: I have been using a different Andalou moisturizer that didn't have any tint and I loved it so much that I wanted to try more of their products. I've only used this once so far and I already love it as well. The "sheer nude" shade is perfect for my skin tone (I'm usually the second lightest shade on a basic skin spectrum) and it does a nice job of covering redness on my chin, cheeks, and forehead. It does have a somewhat greasy finish, but I have yet to find any non-chemical moisturizer with spf that doesn't have some kind of sheen to it; I simply add primer and mattifying powder on top to absorb the shine and it works perfectly. The scent is also quite lovely too. I highly recommend this CC cream for people who want to moisturize, protect, and even out their skin tone without tons of harsh chemicals. Great product!

column13: Kills ticks on a dog-falls right off!
column14: I use this all the time on my kids and myself to repel the giant mosquitos we have here.  I don't take time to dilute it, I just dot it around our ankles, wrists, and other exposed skin and it has worked as good as the OFF I used to buy (which is pretty nasty stuff).  But the best thing about this oil, is that it removes/kills ticks on dogs! I have two little outside dogs, and I always keep my yard sprayed, but I try not to put any chemicals on the dogs. I have had them for about seven years, and they have never had fleas or ticks. Yesterday, I was outside and one had a tick on his chin (gross), and I didn't have any tweezers handy.  I had this Insect Shield oil sitting there on the patio table, so I just wet the tick and the area around it with the oil, then went inside. I forgot about it, but went outside in about 6 hours ready to pull the nasty thing out, and it was GONE! Gone, and there was just a red scab on the dog's chin.  So, this oil is amazing!!!  I suppose I can't be sure that it actually killed it, but it got it off the dog and I didn't have to touch it, so it's good stuff to me (and I sprayed the yard that afternoon).

column6: Revlon Hot Air Brush Kit for Styling & Frizz Control
column14: I just received this Revlon hot air brush and I love it! I was afraid that it might be too heavy or loud as other reviewers complained about but not at all! Compared to a regular blow drier which feels very heavy and loud this Revlon Shine enhancing Hot Air Kit feels like a feather (maybe not as light but you get the comparison right?) and for having 1200 watts is surprisingly not too loud. I previously  bought the Infinity Pro Rotating hot air brush by Conair and was very disappointed. The bristles are too soft, it doesn't hold my hair and it's not powerful enough for my type of hair. I have long  curly hair and  before using it I used a regular blow drier until it was about 80 to 90% dry because otherwise the "hot  air" is so cool that  I felt it would never dry my hair or would take forever. End result? A hot mess. It made my hair soooo frizzy. I did the right side with the Infinity Pro and the left side with the John frieda hot air brush and what a difference! The John frieda hot air brush left my hair noticeably better.  Even though they both have 500 watts for some reason the difference was huge. I think the Infinity Pro it's still a good product but for people who have thin straight hair that just want to add some volume. After doing some research I realized that for my type of hair I needed a more powerful hot hair brush and that's why I decided to give this Revlon hot air brush a chance. I haven't done my full hair with it but wanted to test out the frequent complaints I saw such as weight and noise. I will update my review as soon I do my whole hair with it, can't wait!

column6: Paula's Choice SKIN BALANCING Ultra-Sheer Daily Defense SPF 30 Oil-Free Moisturizer with Antioxidants for Oily Skin - 2 oz
column13: I like it, but not like loving it
column14:
I have been using this for the past two weeks. So far, I like it, but not like loving it.
I bought this with the intention of layering it under my physical sunscreen; I figured it's the summer and double protection can never hurt. BTW, I have normal skin with occasional break out from the warm weather, menstruation, and stress...
Pros:
very light, dry touch, no white cast (like those from physical sunscreen), fast absorbed, no fragrance...
Cons:
sting my eyes, NO MOISTURIZTION (you def NEED to apply face moisturizer despite the fact it claims to be a moisturizer), cause those white things when you are still trying to spread it even and generously on my face...

I suggest only use it in the summer, wait for it to be absorbed for a good 5 mins or so before you put make up on. Do not let it get near to your eye area, OUCH!

UPDATED:
went to the pool ystday with my boyfriend who has extremely sensitive skin and rosacea. I put this on his face before we headed out. He had allergy reaction within 10 mins that he had to wash it off immediately.... so steer cleared if you have rosacea too.

column13: A good choice for smaller heads, though the wig is not very full, we are pleased w/the purchase because the hair is very nice
column14:
This wig is a bit thin, and it won't fit an adult male well - putting it on, it was so tight we knew it could not be worn by my son for any length of time.
That said, we were looking to combine two wigs, so this one became the one that we decided to use for parts, so it is still ok and we are still happy with our purchase, as the hair is good quality and a good color for a white wig. It takes styling well, just remember it is synthetic hair and needs cool styling methods only. I like to use Got2Be for spiking. Silver White, btw, is really closer to bright white. The inner mesh was cream.

Note- for those interested in stitching into or from this wig.
We often combine more than one wig to get a look we want; often spiking a wig or cutting it will reveal the inner wigcap, so adding extra hair prevents this, and sometimes we add extra hair to keep props in place, in this case, extra hair will be used to keep goggles in place and looking good. This wig is one of 2 combined for a 'Gunner" look. It was fairly easy to disassemble this wig- it was a bit delicate but all wigs are, however, it was not hard to get the hair off of it, and stitching it into a 2nd wig cap was fairly easy.

column13: PT Muscle Jelly is the BEST for pain relief
column14: I have any number of products from Plant Therapy. If I was only allowed to buy one (which I hope wouldn't happen,) it would be the Muscle Aloe Jelly! I LOVE, LOVE, LOVE it. I'm a fine crafter and have damaged my wrists through all of the repetitive movement. Also have issues with my shoulders as a result of playing racquet sports for years. Stopped doing upper body workouts as a result. Around the first of the year, I started taken Pilates classes. Have become so enamored with it that I do a class every day. Now, I'm working to rebuild my wrists and shoulders. I started doing aromatherapy in April to help deal with pain, and other, issues. I apply my "pain blend" before and after class, and as needed the rest of the day. You're supposed to rotate what you use every few weeks. Originally, the Muscle Aloe Jelly was in the rotation. It works so well, that I save it for when I REALLY need it. I have to say that my wrists and shoulders have improved a lot as a result of the work I've been doing. I have the Muscle Aloe Jelly to thank for that. If I couldn't alleviate the pain, I couldn't work out every day.  I started my EO journey a little over 3 months ago. After attending a disappointing presentation by a rep from an mlm company. It spurred me on to do my own research. I came across Plant Therapy (PT) and choose it as my go to company for essential oils. I made this choice because they espouse safe usage (have hired one of the go to people on using EOs safety as a consultant who also developed their "kids safe" line), have trained aromatherapists on staff to answer questions, support a fabulous FB page on safe usage, etc. PT really thinks of the little touches, the EO bottles have labels on the top with the names of the oils/synergies. Trust me, it really makes it easier to find what you want/need as your collection grows. You don't have to pick up each oil and read the name. You can just glance from above. On top of that, they always offer free shipping!  I received this product for a discount in exchange for an honest review.

column6: Neutrogena Cleansing Oil-Free Eye Makeup Remover
column14: I purchased this makeup remover to replace a free sample bottle of Lancome Bi-Facil Makeup Remover, which worked excellently but was a little expensive.  The Neutrogena makeup remover is considerably less expensive, but doesn't work nearly as well.  I use it almost exclusively to remove my non-waterproof, dual-layer mascara (Covergirl Bombshell Volume).  Pros: 1. Doesn't dry out skin. 2. Doesn't burn eyes. 3. It's oil-free. Cons: 1. Requires a good deal of scrubbing, even with mascara that isn't waterproof. 2. If you use a dual-layer mascara, and you're not vigilant about making sure you remove every single bit of mascara every single day, this makeup remover will NOT be able to handle the buildup of the volume layer.  (I'll admit here that I'm a tough customer here: I don't remove my makeup except when I shower, and that means I occasionally freshen up by putting on another layer of mascara without removing the first layer.  If you do this, the Neutrogena makeup remover will NOT be able to remove the mascara.) 3.  You have to use a LOT of this stuff for it to be effective.  Overall: my reaction is "eh."  It's fine, it works ok, it's inexpensive, whatever.  I'd trade some of the gentleness for more makeup-removing power, and I'll keep shopping around for something better.  If your mascara situation is very simple (non-waterproof, single layer mascara that you wash off between applications), it might work for you.

column6: Garnier Nutrisse Ultra Color Nourishing Hair Color Creme, R2 Medium Intense Auburn (Packaging May Vary)
column13: R2 - Gorgeous but does not rinse out!
column14:
Ok, so I don't ever color my hair but I wanted something a little different so I figured I'd give it a go.

I'll start by saying I LOVE the color. It's shiny and gorgeous.

Now let's move on to what I do not like. This list is considerably longer. First of all, the gloves that come with this hair dye are terrible. One of them tore, but it was up by the cuff so I didn't worry about it. The dye actually seeped through the gloves and turned my hands red. Fortunately, it washed off relatively easily.

Let's move on to the dyeing experience. The dye was easy to mix up, and it didn't have too offensive of an odor. That was cool. When it came time to rinse the dye from my hair, I'm a little embarrassed to say that I found it amusing just how much my bathtub resembled a violent crime scene. My husband helped me rinse my hair, which was helpful. 45 minutes later, the water was still tinted as it came off my hair. I was starting to get cranky. I feel as if it should not have taken so long. Finally, some time later, I felt confident enough that my hair was fully rinsed, and I wrapped it up in a towel. Bad move. The towel got stained. Fortunately, I always wash my towels in bleach, so this didn't bother me so much. My hair looked gorgeous.

Fast forward almost three weeks. My hair still looks gorgeous. It's still shiny and hasn't lost it's luster. Unfortunately, it is also STILL staining my towels and sheets after about 2 dozen showers. I am extremely confused by this, and also saddened by it. I do not feel like I will want to purchase this hair color again in the future.

column6: Henckels Classic Inox manicure kit, pocket case, black neat's leather, 3 pcs. # 97505-004
column13: Tools seem worth the price, won't know for awhile if they last
column14:
I was looking at every review for cuticle scissors on Amazon and kept seeing people say things like \\\These are almost as good as my old Henckels\\\\\" or \\\\\"I wish these were as thin as my old Henckels\\\\\". I'd never heard of Henckels, but my wife had and she thought they were good. So I went looking for them on Amazon and found them, but almost none of their products have reviews. So I took a risk despite the $60 price, because I like to buy things that last.

The scissors in this kit are indeed very sharp and very thin for getting close to cuticles. The construction is very solid with no wiggle. The file has a rougher and smoother side that both do better on nails than anything else I've used. The tweezers... well, I haven't used that yet.

The real test of these tools will be how well they hold their edge so I'll have to update this review in a year or two, but for now I give them 5 stars.

If you balk at the price of this kit, you can also find the individual tools for less: [[ASIN:B006HCRDX2 $31.50 Henckels Classic Inox Combination nail scissors, polished # 47540-091]], [[ASIN:B006HCREAO $13.90 Henckels Twin Classic sapphire nail file 3 1/2'', polished # 88330-091]], and [[ASIN:B003ZUKZS4 $17.50 Henckels TWINOX Tweezers, squared-off, Stainless steel, satin-finish # 78148-101]]

But it's cheaper per tool if you buy the kit and the case is really nice. It's actual leather and all the stitching is high quality. The only issue is where the leather wraps around an edge, where a crease in the scale pattern sits right on the 90 degree edge, the leather has split. It's not noticeable unless you look carefully, but I worry it might continue to rip over time. We'll see.

Henckels is a German company that's been around over 100 years. This kit shipped from Germany so it took a little while, maybe two weeks. Shipping was $7.50 per tool but if you buy additional tools/kits, it won't raise shipping.

You can find kits on Amazon containing many many combinations of Henckels tools but many of them are really hard to find unless you know the name of the kit. Searching for just \\\\\"Henckels\\\\\" gets you all sorts of irrelevant results. I discovered that if I clicked the word \\\\\"Henckels\\\\\" in any of the tool listings it brought me to a page showing all the tools and all the kits with tools. Except when I do that now, it brings me to a different page listing categories of Henckels products, of which they display 30 different knife categories but no manicure categories. Hopefully they'll fix that.

BTW, I was confused seeing a couple of different brands carrying \\\\\"Inox\\\\\" manicure tools and thought it might be a type of metal or a style... But it's just a European way of saying \\\\\"Inoxidizable\\\\\" which is more commonly known in the US as \\\\\"Stainless\\\\\" or rust proof.kits on Amazon containing many many combinations of Henckels tools but many of them are really hard to find unless you know the name of the kit. column14: My hair... How to describe my hair. Unruly? The worst? My husband refers to it as lioness. The lion's mane.. And probably in his mind, frizz ball. I have only been using it for a few weeks, and I usually wash my hair every 4-5 days (because of this it doesn't get oily as fast) but I style it sometimes 2-3 times between washes. It is lightweight and it smells HEAVENLY. I cannot figure out what it smells like but it makes me do a double sniff (think double take but sniff style). Tonight I let me hair air dry after using this and while it is still frizzy (I have NEVER found a product that makes it frizzless), it is so much more calm than usual! Just get some. column13: My crappy thin hair has not magically turned into a full ...
column14:
I will try to keep this review up to date.

8/14/2015
So far I have been using it about a week. My crappy thin hair has not magically turned into a full head of hair so thick my fingers get stuck, but it smells nice and I do think using a good shampoo is important especially for people with hair loss. I am a young white male, started losing my hair when I was about 15. Didn't think much of it until I was in my early twenties and I saw the top of my head on one of those grocery store security cameras when you walk in the front door. I quickly realized my uncanny resemblance to George Costanza. Unfortunately I suffer a lack of talent and am unable to pull of that look, God bless him. Not prepared to go full on Patrick Stewart at 21 I started using Minoxidil. It seems to have hit its point of usefulness. My hair is no longer falling out but my hopes of it ever returning to it's youthful state are long gone. I have been using the DHT blocking shampoo by Pura d'or (Blue Label) which I will link below. I used that for quite some time and did not notice any improvement but combined with the minoxidil I was not noticing any hair loss which was good. I saw other reviewers on different websites talk about how the Pura d'or definitely worked for stopping hair loss but not in aiding growth. The common consensus was the vitamins, DHT blocker and proprietary hair growth chemicals in this shampoo actually helped to grow new hair unlike the others. I ended up buying the 3 pack because of the cost savings, so only time will tell if it helps or not. If it doesn't I will likely return to a more affordable DHT blocking shampoo.

Pura d'or Blue Label
http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0079R6BD2?psc=1&redirect=true&ref_=oh_aui_detailpage_o02_s00

column14: I wanted to wait a couple of months before I wrote a review so I could really check this gadget out. If I could give it 10 stars, I would! My feet were not in bad shape, but this beats any other products I have used by far. In fact, the only other time my feet felt so good was after a pedicure at a salon. I used it twice a week for the first two weeks, then backed off to once per week and even longer. I had a corn on the bottom of a big toe that I worked at slowly for the first couple weeks - about 4 times. I have not had the callous return there like it had been before and now it is just a quick pass over that area to keep it smooth. It has been about 3 1/2 months and I am still on the same set of AA batteries that I put in to start. Using this fantastic tool followed with a nice cream or lotion and my feet feel wonderful, look great. Don't let this power file fool you as it can leave a tender spot if you push it against your skin. I love mine and will not be without one again.

column6: MELODYDERM¬Æ CAVIAR CREAM - Best Firming & Anti-Age Cream - Rich In Antioxidants - Effectively Reduces Wrinkles & Fine Lines - Deeply Moisturizes & Hydrates the Skin - With Caviar Extract + Collagen + Shea Butter - Gives a Glowing & Radiant skin - Luxurious & Nutritious Skin Care 30g
column14:
I am a sucker for facial creams and serums, but this caviar cream is one of the best moisturizers I have had for a long time. It is definitely comparable to the cosmetcell moisturizer I used to buy back in Europe. The prize difference is extensive though, I used to pay $300 for that cream. This one is fraction of the cost but does the same job and feels the same way when applied on skin. It sinks into the skin in seconds and is best applied before bed. It is thick and like all thick creams - little goes a long way. I have used it for 10 days and it has made my skin feel smooth and well nourished. My skin is glowing and the acne scars I had are smoothing out.
It comes in an adorable pink jar and has almost no smell.
The ingredients are very good. Many well known cosmetic lines do not even have such a great ingredients list.
I am thankful to the Melodyferm for providing me the caviar cream at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased feedback.

column14: I have medium/dark brown hair and wanted to lighten the underside to a bright blonde. This seemed perfect seeing as it was "ULTRA" color MEANT for dark hair! Perfect....WRONG! This barely did anything :( Precisely followed the directions and all this did was lighten my hair maybe 1 shade...now I have an odd two toned hair instead of a vivid bright underside popping through. Now I'm trying to figure out if I should just go ahead and bleach it or find another dye to go over this one....sigh. Not only that, the worst part is was the overpowering odor! Thankfully I was only doing the underside so I was able to put on a mask to combat the odor and had to work in the back of my head to get the hair away from my face. REALLY bad. column6: LISCIO Crystal Cream Straighteners & Neutralizer - Normal
column13: This stuff is a godsend for anyone! Even African American hair!
column14: I love the product! I just wish it was on Prime! I'm African American/Asian mixed and it leaves my hair soft and shiny and silky and MUCH easier to manage. I can literally wash and go, unlike the lie that usual relaxers promote. I have been using this for a year now and it's amazing. I would recommend buying a separate protection cream by the same company if you have curly, coarse, dry hair in order to protect your hair. I wouldn't recommend doing this on hair that uses full on relaxers already. I went from texlaxed to this and my hair was fine. Just do your research and know your chemistry. I'm not going to lie, I did a year of research and growing out my hair before getting this done. Most if not all salons are hesitant on doing this on African American hair so I would recommend a beautician who knows how to do hair for all races and they are LICENSED! The reason why I say this is because my beautician says that the steps and the way that the product reacts and smells reminds her of when she is giving perms for her white customers.

When I first began shaving as a teenager, my father bought me an electric shaver. It was a Remington, and one that I used for years. Later on, I received a free Gillette Mach 3, and began using a more traditional razor for shaving my face. I never even considered using an electric razor after that, and used the Fusion and other razors that Gilette introduced.

Time went on, and I remembered the benefit of using an electric razor. I remember being able to shave faster and, obviously, it's easier to shave in other locations as you're doing things. I remember never having as close of a shave, but figured it would be good for some days.

My initial use was after not shaving in nearly a week (I usually shave every other day). I applied some electric pre-shave to my face and went to work. While the initial time it probably took as long as it would with my Fusion, I was very surprised by how smooth my face felt. I'd never had an electric razor this good. There were a few spots afterwards that weren't amazing, but they weren't bad. I could deal with them. Sometimes I run into that with the Gillette anyway.

I've continued to use it almost every other day since (now about two weeks). I've been impressed. As time has gone on, as expected, I've been able to shave faster than I usually did. The convenience is nice, and I love being able to just rinse it out with water afterwards. So easy! I've yet to have had to charge it again.

Needless to say, I'm glad I picked this up. Technology has improved over years, and I'm glad to see that has occurred with razors. It's exactly what I was hoping for. Don't hesitate to pick this up if you're in need of a good, nicely priced electric razor. 2015-08-14 US 40436489 R30OLDAFBAKNF7 B0087A5BA4 301109787 DINAIR AIRBRUSH EYE SHADOW MAKEUP - 1 Bottle ORCHID PLUM.25oz. column13: I may be in love with this contour kit!!!
column14:
I am actually surprised and shocked by the pigments in the different colors in this Contor set. The fact and I could open it up and not see a oily condensation on top made me very happy.

The lighter colors are a perfect creamy consistency for my wet blending sponge, and I definitely was not expecting that for the price. I will say that it is comparable to one of the higher end Contor sets that I have purchased, especially the darker colors. Since I am more of a honey or olive skin tone, the darker colors are perfect for contouring my chin, my cheeks and my neck. Again, definitely not what I was expecting for the price of this Contor set. I'm happy and surprised and grateful that I don't have to spend a ridiculous amount of money on a con tors that that will do the same thing that this one will do for a third of the price!

I compare this to my Anastasia Beverly Hills contour said in, and seven out of the eight colors were exactly the same, pigments and all. I love a cream contour set because I always use a wet blending sponge. I have to honestly say that this is definitely comparable to the one that I spent $55 on. Which is absurd! I'm not angry, but I might be slightly frustrated.

I would tell anyone who is looking for a good contour said that this is probably a really really good way to start, or even if you are a professional makeup artist, that this is a good one to keep on hand. Because it is comparable to the higher end ones.

I received this product at a discounted rate for an honest review.

column6: Elizabeth Arden Red Door 25 Eau de Parfum Spray for Women, 3.3 Ounce
column13: AMAZON, Love You, BUT... I WANT MY MONEY BACK - Beyond Disappointed!
column14: Before opening, but having been a Red Door perfume lover for decades, I wrote a brief review upon receipt of the package.  As stated in my original, unfortunate 5 star review, I did not open the 25th Anniversary bottle until I finished the last bottle.  I was under the impression that the Anniversary Red Door eau de parfum was the exact same fragrance as always, just a larger bottle at a great price because of the anniversary.  Wrong, wrong, wrong.  I don't remember the description saying this was a new and difference fragrance when I ordered on July 12, 2015.  Did I miss that?  I AM WRITING THIS UPDATE ON 12/13/2015.  Don't know why the date of review says August 13, 2015.  WHY CAN'T I EDIT AN ENTIRE REVIEW, AMAZON???  The smell is awful.  It is nothing like the original Red Door - toilette nor eau de parfum.  Note:  I wanted to write this in my first paragraph, but this site won't allow me to do that.  The description said "Limited Edition"'.  So I naturally thought that it was the same scent as always -- just a special size and limited offer for the 25th anniversary.  Sweet Cyn, in her July 2015 review, has the same sentiments about the smell as myself.  When I sprayed it on (tried two different times) I had to wash it off.  I would never go out smelling like that.  I called His n' Her, thinking I might have received a 'defective' bottle.  The man I spoke with was very nice and told me that this scent was changed from the original.  He also said that the eau de parfum was no longer being manufactured and that anyone that gets it now (from any source) would be getting something that was about 3 years old.  And unfortunately, because I did not open this upon receipt, it is too late to return.  I am out money and stuck with a perfume I ordered that I will never use because of a deceptive name.  It's headed for the trash.  Amazon, I know it's not your fault, and I continue to order things from Amazon.  But because of my love of Red Door eau de parfum and using it almost exclusively for well over 20 years, my disappointment is huge.

column14:
I was super excited to try this and the formula was pretty nice and packaging was beautiful and quality. The color is definitely darker than expected and it is a bit shiny for my taste and made me want to wash my face.

I have sensitive, dry, combo skin and it covered redness pretty well and was hydrating.....BUT when I woke up the next day the entire lower half of my face was covered in a ton of tiny little red bumps that burned! Over the next few days they all turned into little tiny white heads and I was putting poison ivy cream on my face to stop the itching and burning. I'm a makeup artist and putting makeup over it before going to a client's house was not only extremely embarrassing, but it felt like my face was on fire.

I'm guessing this is quite rare but I had a similar reaction on a smaller scale to another product from a different company that was also made with fruit pigments so I'm guessing I have an allergy to these kinds of cosmetics. So bummed as I really think 100% Pure makes nice quality products...just wish my skin wasn't so darn picky. :(

column6: Maybelline New York Volum'express The Colossal Chaotic Lash
column13: Not enough payoff -- had to apply at least 10-15 times to build up volume, not very \chaotic\" unless you take your time"
column14:
1-5 applications - thin, wet formula -- not enough deposit onto lashes. Lashes looked darker but that's it.
5-15 applications - more build up for a volumized effect, but not dramatic or "wow" or majorly lifting.
15-20+ applications - if you let the 1st and 2nd round of applications dry, then the "chaotic" irregular effect starts to appear b/c it has some base to "grab" onto.

Overall look: Slightly uneven volume, Slightly uneven clumping, Slightly uneven length/lifting.
Does it look awful? No. Listen--if were a total train wreck effect, Maybelline wouldn't even launch it.
It's the equivalent of a good girl trying to be bad for one night -- from afar, it just looks like normal mascara.

But really, it's not astounding or "wow" in any way. You can achieve the same look by layering 2-3 different mascaras to get that slightly messy effect, and save yourself money.

As we all know, mascaras when freshly opened are still "wet" and fluid. after a month or so, it dries out slightly due to the wand pumping air into the bottle via regular use. I suspect this is when the "Chaotic" look will be acheived with less applications as the dry time affects the buildup of of each layer. The drier each coat, the more "chaos" you'll get.

column6: xtava Allure 2200W Professional Ionic Ceramic Hair Dryer - Bring the Salon to Your Home with This Powerful and Precise Blow Dryer - 2 Speeds - 3 Heat Settings (Ebony)
column14:
LOVE it. Finally a hairdryer that has powerful air, just the right heat settings, and doesn't break the bank. Three heat settings that feel like they should. Cold. Warm. Hot. Two speed settings, high and low. Very happy with the ease of selecting what I want, plus (again) the great air flow.

A major plus is not having the high-pitch screeching whine of a Conair or so many other brands. For such power, the Allure 2200W is a relatively quiet dryer. On a noise scale of 10, I would venture to say between "4" and "6," depending on the settings. For comparison, I would rate most Conairs and probably most other blow dryers I've used at between 7-10. Not dis'ing Conair, just mostly been using that brand for the past decade.

My only wish is that the Allure buttons were on the right side (as opposed to facing inside toward your head), as I find the buttons a tad easy to inadvertently press. But that's a personal preference. Maybe you'll like it just the way it is. On the other hand, if you have both left- and right-handed family members, this might be a good solution.

Either way, I personally love this dryer. Five stars.

I have had horribly calloused feet for my entire life due to going barefoot all the time, even up and down our gravel driveway when I was a kid. My feet's callouses had callouses and they were extremely tough. I saw the commercials for the Amope product and was very excited. Finally something that would give me the soft feet of my dreams... HA! Not a chance. That thing was no match for my iron-clad feet. I was frustrated, and scoped out Amazon for yet another solution and came across this beauty. I was dubious, but read the reviews and figured, what the heck, I'm not spending much $ if it doesn't work. I eagerly awaited the delivery, and when I first took it out I was a bit disappointed. It just looked like a much larger version of the old Pedi-Egg (which kind of worked, but it was a lot of work for little effect). I tried it out anyway...and...WOW!! This thing is a serious power tool! Yeah, it's not motorized, but this baby takes so little effort to shave off years of callouses. I was amazed as the tool quickly revealed baby-soft, pink feet! My mouth was agape and my heart leapt with joy. OK, that's a little over the top but if you've lived with feet like mine you would understand. One of the reviewers told a hilarious cautionary tale about being a bit over-zealous with the scraping and I would back that up. I stopped before I damaged myself but could easily see that one could take it a bit too far and soft would turn to sore. So, be careful, but buy this! You won't be disappointed! I am returning my Amope and I'm stocking up on these puppies! (Though this thing is of such industrial strength I think if I bought just a couple more I'd probably be set up for baby-soft, pink feet for life!)  :)

column6: Ardell Hair Color Bottle, Unred, 1 Ounce
column13: Add UNRED to 9 Blonde to go from a 7 Dark Sandy Blonde to 9 Beige/Neutral ever-so-slight ash result
column14:
I use this on a guy's hair which is 50%-60% grey with a dark sandy blonde natural color, which is about a 7-8 BG color on Goldwell's topchic chart. I use the packets (2ml each) and just now found the 1oz bottle, here, and ordered it.

1oz is 600 drops. The packets are 2ml so they're pre-measured at 40 drops per packet, I use a brush instead of a bottle as this thickens the color, makes it look like black ink (doesn't stain, for me anyway).

I've tried using 30vol with 9NN & 9A, the hair turns brassy brass and becomes a shade closer to 10G to 10RG or K (copper), too light and very brassy, especially brassy on the roots. I've figured out a formula for a guy's "sandy blonde" color. Here's the formula that finally works for me.

Step 1: I use "Color Fix" by "One n' Only", first (unless I'm out of Color Fix, then I use 30Vol with UNRED), applying color fix to roots first, for the first 10 minutes trying to remain only on the roots then apply to remainder of head. This remains on the head for 20-30 minutes (can go longer or multiple times to remove pigment). 30 minutes brings a 7 to a 9 or 10, the hair arrives at a pale banana yellow color... I like the color it arrives at at this point, I'd rather just tone it and make the color a perfect 10 but he wants a blend between Sahara Beige (9GB) and Tourmaline (9GN) and NO Golds or Reds detected at all, otherwise I have to start over, if he sees any reds/brass, I have to start over. So, I have to adjust everything each time I color his hair. The Color Fix removes pigment but it doesn't damage his hair, I'm not sure how Color Fix works without damaging but it does indeed work. It helps to use Dual Senses Shampoo/Cond+Treatment & Moroccanoil daily. Unred mixed with Conditioner once a week.

Step 2: I use 20Vol developer and 9BG/9NN with 1 packet of "Ardell" "Unred", the color arrives perfectly as a 9 neutral with little ash... USUALLY. When I'm out of "Color Fix", I have to repeat step 1 two or three times to pull it as a pale yellow using 30 vol, 30vol is SO HARSH!

On occasion, when reds or coppers appear but are not so intense that I have to start over, I use Unred with 10A and 10-20Vol as a toner, this usually works perfectly, depending on what he's been using in his hair between colors. I notice that if he uses certain shampoo / conditioner, his hair will become brassy within 30 days.

Step 3 is toner: 10A with 1 packet Ardell Unred using 10Vol (or 20Vol for 1 level lift) to tone out any remaining gold/red/copper hues.

Step 4: Once a week, after shampooing, equal amounts of Unred and Goldwell DualSenses conditioner applied to towel dried hair cuts brassy buildup, 5 minutes letting it sit on hair then rinse, it works and doesn't turn blue! Many kinds of red cutting products will turn hair blueish.

I notice that 1 packet of UNRED (or 40 drops of UNRED) is usually the only amount needed for moving from a 7 to a proper 9. For every step along the way, I use the UNRED additive with 5 pumps of Goldwell SilkLift Serum, his hair, even though its processing several times, is an excellent condition because of the products being used.

If your hair is red or really copper, this UNRED will help, you may have to use 80 drops (2 packets) for best results.f "Color Fix", I have to repeat step 1 two or three times to pull it as a pale yellow using 30 vol, 30vol is SO HARSH!

column6: Pedi Electronic Foot File Callus Remover for Dry Feet Shaves Dead Hard Cracked Skin & Calluses on Feet, Show Immediate Results for Man & Woman (Blue)
column13: More than worth the cost, a must get for your feet
column14:
Read the reviews and came into this product with pretty high expectations, and purchased it for my son who has very bad callouses. His review follows:

After receiving it today, I read through the instructions (thorough and understandable), installed the batteries (easy to accomplish) and went outside to have some good lighting and to avoid having skin fly everywhere inside. I switched to the grinding head before starting off to work on the callouses, and goodness the skin was just flying off like I was taking an electric sander to a rough piece of wood. After working on them for about 10 minutes all told (going from callous to callous and then starting all over again more times than I could keep count on) there was very noticeable progress on all of the callouses. I then switched to the standard head and worked on the whole of each foot to finish off my first use of the product.

After heading in and washing off my feet I was overjoyed by how much better my feet looked after just this first go. The soles and heels were much smoother and looked considerably better than they had before I started, and my horrid, rough and ugly callouses were mostly smoothed over. I expect it will take having a go at it every day for perhaps up to a week before I can get the callouses completely ground down but the improvement is astounding. Even with all the work I put the rollers through they seem to have plenty of life left in them, and cleanup was just as easy as the instructions indicated.

I would highly recommend getting this product if you have rough feet and/or callouses. I fully intend to purchase replacement rollers to have on hand so I can keep my feet in good condition once I get them there, which shouldn't take long. At this stage, I can't think of any negatives, as even as a man with big hands the unit is comfortable to hold.

column13: Comfy and helps me sleep. Strap could be a bit better.
column14:
I honestly didn‚Äôt think I‚Äôd like this mask very much because of the way it looked. It‚Äôs a padded mask with spaces inside for your eyes and a small indentation for your nose/nose bridge. The strap is a thin garter with Velcro. That is the one thing that I feel should be improved. I have a smaller head so I attach this as close to the end of the Velcro for the most secure fit. column14: [[VIDEOID:d848a750fe3dce8ce65d1db4ffb98eeb]]  I'm not a huge fan of false lashes, but I wanted my lashes to be full, long, and voluminous without all the gunky glue and loss of my real lashes. Does not irritate my eyes or interfere with my contacts.  Best of all, this product is all-natural. No need for heavy, eye-lashing ripping extensions.  I extend the natural way!  The best part is that this product is water resistant and I can easily remove it with my 100% pure rosewater with any difficulty whatsoever.  Highly recommend to the woman that wants sexier, longer, and thicker lashes the natural way.  ***I received this product in exchange for my honest and unbiased review

column6: Facial Serum and Cream Kit by Ageless La Cure - Natural, Organic, Hydrating, Lifting and Toning by Phyto 5, 1.5 Ounce
column13: Love how these feel on my sensitive skin!
column14:
I do love Phyto skin care products. I don't wear face make-up, have very dry/sensitive skin, and this Facial Serum & Cream Kit is luxury for my face/skin. Typically, my skin soaks up most other products quickly - or the product is SO greasy, it lays on top of my skin (attracting small bugs or lint to stick to my face). Back to THIS beautiful product.

It arrives in a cellophane-wrapped simple white box. Open the lid to find the two simple white tube inside. Yes, the packaging conveys clean and pure, but since those parts are discarded...I'd much rather have a bit more product since this is pricey (currently offered on Amazon at $168).

For night time...after lightly washing my skin, I shake the serum bottle and give two pumps of product to my fingertips. Gently massage in - let dry. Give two pumps of the cream - lightly massage into my face/neck. (Because I am SO dry, two pumps does not give me the coverage Phyto intends, but I'm also curious how long these will last - and will post an update).

For day time... after rinsing face, two pumps of just the cream.

I am very pleased with how delicately and smooth it spreads and soaks into my skin. My skin/face feels moisturized all day (which is RARE...live in a drought-area, summertime, zero humidity). High praise for this! Thank you.

The only downside for me (other than the high price) is I am not a big fan of rose scent - and these definitely have a rose scent. While it does dissipate quickly, I prefer a light citrus or ginger type of scent...if any.

It makes this claim::: " The Ageless Facial Serum and Cream Kit by Phyto 5 is a revolutionary duo which works together to fill-in wrinkles, hydrate, firm and restructure skin. The Les 5 Secrets Serum with commiphora extract, traditionally used in Ayurveda medicine, smoothens wrinkles and gently mixes with natural essential oils of rose and apricot to provide major hydration and anti-aging treatment. The Les 5 Secrets cream with acacia gum, cupuacu butter, shea butter and precious essential oils of rose and squalane hydrate, firm and restructure, achieving radiant and younger looking skin. "

If you're seeking a deeply hydrating facial-skin care product without any greasiness, and the price isn't a factor, do give this product a try. I will update after a few weeks to see if I can attest to filled-in wrinkles (I'm 63), firmer, and a younger/ restructured skin.

***Update three weeks later...I do love the feel of this product - hydrating without being greasy. Left my face feeling comfortable throughout the day (and night after p.m. application). I cannot, however, report that it changed my skin to firmer, younger/restructured. If it wasn't so pricey, I would continue with it for all the positives I do notice.r, shea butter and precious essential oils of rose and squalane hydrate, firm and restructure, achieving radiant and younger looking skin. column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14: This shaver is definitely great, you can tell its built to last just by how it feels in your hand. Quality materials and a solid feel are your first thoughts when unboxing the shaver. One thing that should be made clear to anyone deciding to purchase, the cleaner base is large and requires ample ample space near an electrical outlet. You will also need to purchase additional cleaner packs to replenish after you run out and these run for about 25 bucks for 3. Now as far as a shaver goes I am a complete face and head shaver, meaning as a balding male I use this shaver to keep my head clean as well as my face. It does a very good job keeping a close neat shave, does not nick or pinch my skin and has a very helpful trimmer for my goatie. I do however feel that at this price point(over 300 hundred bucks) it could be even better. I do not feel a completely smooth stubble free shave by touch but in the mirror there is no visible hair. The cleaner is a great feature but is very load so keep that in mind if you plan on running it at night with kids or people sleeping. Overall this is a great shaver, Braun continues to set the bar very high. This is by far the best electric shaver I have ever used and the best part is I received this shaver as part of a promotion from Braun and BzzAgent! Lucky me =)

column6: Carapex After Bath Lotion with Aloe and Shea Butter
column13: It absorbs easily and leaves my skin feeling soft
column14:
You might say I'm picky about lotions. The way the make my skin feel after they absorb is very important. This lotion was a winner for me. It's rich and creamy. It absorbs easily and leaves my skin feeling soft, not greasy. I also love the idea of after bath lotion. When you take a nice hot bath, you are opening up all of the pores on your skin, and then putting on this hydrating lotion that can now get deeper into your skin and really work. It's packed with great healthy ingredients like shea butter, aloe vera, soybean oil, vitamin E and Japanese green tea extract.There are no artificial or harmful ingredients. Another thing that's a plus for me is that it's unscented. I have asthma and a lot of scents bother me or take my breath away. There's no risk with this lotion of getting a scent you don't like. I'm very happy with this product.
I received this product for free in exchange for an honest and unbiased review.

column6: Sundown Vitamin E Oil 70000 IU
column13: Not pure organic/natural vitamin E .. wish I realized this before purchase...
column14:
THIS IS NOT PURE VITAMIN E. It contains tocopheryl acetate irritating to skin, causing redness, rashes, and potential allergic reactions. According to the Cosmetic Ingredient Review (CIR) of the ingredient, tocopheryl acetate helped protect against oxidative damage, but produced skin sensitizing or skin irritating effects in one animal study. A 1991 study detailed four cases of contact dermatitis caused by cosmetic creams that contained tocopheryl acetate.
The CIR, though it concluded that tocopheryl was safe for cosmetics, also noted that studies with the ingredient demonstrated some ‚Äúenhancement of photocarcinogenesis,‚Äù which means it may actually encourage the carcinogenic effects of UV rays.
High doses of this ingredient have also been found in animal studies to cause tumor formation. Though that‚Äôs not likely to be a concern if you‚Äôre using only a little of the ingredient, as in most personal care products, the concern is the potential buildup over time. We simply don‚Äôt have the necessary safety studies on this ingredient when used for several times a day over many years.

column6: Best All Natural Mineral Sunscreen. Chemical Free & Hypoallergenic. Moisturizing & Fragrance-free. Kid & Reef Safe. SPF 30
column14:
I really love this stuff and smother my face, neck, chest, lips, hands and feet in it any time I can. The jar seems small but it really is not smaller than almost of the lotions in tubes because it contains the same weight. The difference is that this goes much further than any others I have tried. You pay for what you get and in this particular case you get a little luxury built in as well. It leaves my skin soft, invigorated and drenched in healthy ingredients. Just place a small dot on you forehead, cheeks, nose, chin, neck and chest. Don't forget your lips and ears. By the time you have done the dots, this scrumptious, smooth lotion has warmed up to skin temperature and spreads easily and deliciously. No white stuff unless you really goop it on and even then the white goes away in time. The slightest most delicate aroma of coconut and the whispery feel of nourishing oils makes me want to just keep applying it. And I do. Even at night! I highly recommend this lotion and I am happy to report that I have not experienced any sunburn during my hour long dog walk every morning. I don't hang out in the sun for longer than that now that I am old enough to understand that it is simply not a good idea. For full disclosure, I am not an acquaintance, friend or family of anyone even remotely involved with The Yellow Bird company and I have not been paid to write this review. I hope my review helps make your buying decision easier.

Update
October 24th, 2015
Have been using this product as described above for over two months now. I still have some left but I am ordering more today. I am convinced that this is the best lotion for my skin. Sun or not. In addition to all the good stuff mentioned above, I need to add that it has done wonders for the skin around my eyes and I love that it does irritate them. Everything else has. It has evened out my skin tone and I even think that it has reduced my broken capillaries - the look of them anyway. I also feel veryprotected from the elements while taking long walks with the dog now that the cold winds are here. I will be using it all winter long. Thank you Yellow Bird Company. I am so glad I found you!

column6: Mavala Switzerland Mavala Stop Nail Biting
column13: An effective treatment for nail biters that will make you fear your own fingers
column14:
As intended, this product has finally brought an end to my lifelong nail biting habit. Shortly after my very first application, my mind wandered and I made the horrible mistake of putting my finger into my mouth to bite my nail as per usual. The taste of Mavala Stop is absolutely horrific and is easily one of the most vile things I have ever tasted. Bitter, repulsive, and lingering are words that can be used to describe this product if it manages to reach your mouth. It only took a few days of this for me to gain an awareness of my nail biting and this awareness has enabled me to stop biting my nails. I have stopped myself numerous times raising my fingers to my mouth, haunted by the memories of previous encounters with Mavala Stop in my mouth and on my lips. Did I mention the taste of this product lingers? It will terrorize your taste buds for at least 20 minutes and is nearly impossible to get the taste out.

If you cook frequently, make sure to wear gloves at all times when using Mavala Stop! I have ruined a couple of meals by forgetting that I had applied this product to my nails and the entire dish was ruined. This stuff is extremely potent and will easily taint food if prepared with bare hands.

I really wish I had the willpower to stop biting my nails without the aid of a horrible tasting product but I don't so this product was a last resort for me. After a month of using Mavala Stop, I have been cured of my nail biting habit. I only hope that I never relapse and never have to use this product again.

column14: I thought i had rosacea on my nose, it would always get red and puffy all the time, I went to the dermatologist and he confirmed that it indeed was. I figured my dad and his brothers had it too. I thought it was pimples or zits so I would try to pop them only to find out I couldn't, leaving this really bad dark scars behind. I couldn't deal with it anymore it got so bad to the point I could not go out in public with out a band aid covering the big red shiny bumps it would create on my nose. I tried changing my diet and it worked but I could not go on longer than a week depriving myself from my favorite foods. As soon as I this certain food it came back. I looked up reviews online trying to find creams that would help reduce my rosacea and the dark scars it left me. This cream would pop up everywhere in every website I would go on. I saw it was also really cheap compared to this other creams that aren't any cheaper than $80. I bought this cream 2 weeks ago and been using it ever since. My nose has not turned red at all since, I have not gotten any of the big disgusting bumps I used to get and it has reduced my dark scars slowly. It has also helped my skin looked younger since it used to look really dry and wrinkly from upclose due to all the previous acidic creams and lotions my doctors would prescribe me. I recommend this cream to any person who has rosacea and has a bit of money to spare, I believe it is worth a try since I took a gamble buying it and it has paid off. I will update this review if anything changes.

column14: This is a fantastic product that I have used for 25 years. It's not easy to find and I've kept it hoarded. Here is a word of caution. You can over treat your hair with Keratin. I had a Salon do 3 treatments in one night and my hair broke because it WILL make your hair brittle. Do NOT use this more than it recommends regardless of the desire to repair your hair. Use coconut oil in between. I had hair extensions and that was how I first came across this product and have sworn by it since. But there is/was a reason it was a licensed  product. Follow the directions and don't over use and be patient. You can't undo all the damage but Emergencee is one of the best products out there that you can find to at least minimize how much hair you may lose.

column6: Fixodent Plus Truefeel Denture Adhesive Cream 2 Oz
column13: Will STICK with My Super PoliGrip Extra Care
column14:
In comparison to Super PoliGrip Extra Care, I find that the Fixodent Plus TrueFeel is anything but. I don't know where they got the name, TrueFeel because it most certainly isn't. This product does not feel like that at all. And there are other complaints I have about it, but I am going to do a comparison between Super PoliGrip Extra Care and Fixodent Plus TrueFeel so you can make a decision which one you want to buy.

The Pros:
When I applied Fixodent to my lower denture, the tip was easy to use unlike PoliGrip's, which is too large. I always have to use the end of a dental floss tool to smooth the adhesive cream out.

(Take a hint Poligrip designers.)

There isn't a strong or nasty taste to either Fixodent or PoliGrip. So that is a plus for Fixodent as well.

The Cons:
When I used Fixodent, no matter how little I used, it oozed out into my mouth, leaving it feeling super gooey. It is extremely hard to get out of my mouth and denture. If I use just the right amount of PoliGrip, that does not happen.

Fixodent Plus TrueFeel Adhesive did not keep food from getting under my lower denture while eating. Fixodent, in fact, held particles of food inside the adhesive that caused me a lot of discomfort, especially when eating chips or anything with seeds. However, it holds my upper in quite well with no food getting under my lower plate.

Fixodent did not stay in very long. I would say about 35 minutes. When I ate, it would lose it's hold allowing my lower denture to wobble and come loose, but it held my upper denture in for the whole time I wore it.

I feel pretty safe, out in public or during fellowship dinners, with Polident. It stays in for up to 10 hrs.

I thought it might be helpful if I gave you the ingredients of both products.

Fixodent Plus TrueFeel: Calcium/Sodium PVM/MA, Mineral Oil, Cellulose Gum, Petrolatum, Silica

Super PoliGrip Extra Care: Poly (Methylvinylether/Maleic Acid) Sodium-Calcium Mixed Partial Salt, Petrolatum, Cellulose Gum, Mineral Oil (Paraffinum Liquidum), D Alpha Tocopherol Acetate (Vitamin E), Methylparaben, Ethylparaben

I hope these comparisons help you to make the right decision for you. Maybe Fixodent Plus TrueFeel Adhesive would be right for you, if you have properly fitting dentures. But, I am sticking with my Super PoliGrip Extra Care.

I was excited to try this product for free, from Fixodent, for a campaign I'm involved with.

NOTE: Next month I will have both dentures re-lined. column6: ARM & HAMMER Truly Radiant Battery Toothbrush + Toothpaste Pack
column13: UPDATED  This is a difference maker!  I LOVE my CLEANER TEETH!!!
column14:
UPDATE: I had my regular dental checkup / cleaning last night. The hygienist asked if I had changed toothbrushes! She could tell the difference that my teeth were much cleaner, my gums were healthier! I have four gaps where my gums are receding, and three these gaps were measurably smaller! Both my dentist and hygienist were SO HAPPY!! They both told me to keep using the new toothbrush, and keep using the new brand of toothpaste, because my teeth are so much better than before!

THIS SET IS A WINNER!!!!
(end update, original review follows)

I did not expect to like this. I expected to try it, review it, and pass it on to my kids (who like power toothbrushes). I've also always been a "Crest guy" - the only brand of toothpaste I've ever bought. And my first impressions were negative: both brushes are identical; how do I know which is mine and which is my wife's? Then I tried it - wet the brush, put the paste on, turned it on - and the toothpaste went flying. So I made a mental note - put the brush in my mouth before turning it on. The "mint" paste is bland - not bad, just not minty that I could tell.

And then I fell in love with this set!!! Why? Simple - when I was finished, my teeth felt SO CLEAN, like I had just left the dentist! I never expected that a new toothbrush and toothpaste could make such a difference. I am not exaggerating when I say that this is a HUGE improvement over the toothbrush and toothpaste that I have been using - and I've always been good about brushing. As I write this, it is five hours since I brushed, and my teeth still feel cleaner than they ever used to (except for the first few days after visiting the dentist).

I can't tell for sure if they are whiter, but my teeth definitely feel CLEANER!!!

There is a small downside, in that it's a little messy when I brush, but totally worth it. And if my wife uses the second brush in the package, I'll put stickers or something on them so we can tell them apart. But I seriously LOVE how clean my teeth feel now!I seriously LOVE how clean my teeth feel now!

column14: [[VIDEOID:e3f8e3c7d7e98e502cc3c4af65c6e32a]]I am loving this rechargeable sonic cleanser. At first I wasn't sure what a simple looking tool can do to my face but once I tried it, I loved it! The package comes with the sonic cleaning brush, a velvet drawstring carrying bag, a universal charger and a nice stretchy headband to keep your hair back when cleansing your face. The sonic cleanser is made with soft silicon and the brush part has a good texture that gives a deep clean. The back has a pretty sea shell like design. Before using the sonic cleanser, you'll have to fully charge it, as it does not come charged. When it's charging, you will see a blue light go on, on the bottom. You will know when it's fully charged because it makes a sound and the blue light goes off. The product features an on and off button that's located in the middle and different setting pulse. - setting for a less intense pulse and a + setting for a more intense pulse. I like to apply my moisturizing cleanser right onto the brush and cleanse my face with it for about 1-2 minutes then rinse my it off. When I touched my face, it felt so soft like a baby's butt, no kidding. My face literally felt extremely smooth and I am loving it. I use this everyday, morning and night. I just recently went on a mini family vacation and I had to take this with me. Great product and great price compare to other similar products that are really pricey. I would recommend this. I received this product in exchange for my honest review.

column14:
When I think of Axe personal care products I think of intense, but sexy, men's scents. So when I had to ask if my boyfriend had used it after having it in the shower for several days, you can imagine my surprise when he told me he had been using it but I couldn't even smell anything, even immediately after coming out of the shower. I really had to put my nose up on his skin in order to smell anything. It smells good, but it's VERY faint. In other words, nobody is going to swoon or anything over this product.

I deducted stars not so much for that, but because my boyfriend can't use this as shampoo because he says it dries out his scalp. He can only use it for body wash.

Since the smell isn't strong, I decided to try it on myself after I ran out of my own body wash. Can I just say "holy electric blue, Batman!" This stuff looks like it could glow in the dark, it's such a strange blue color. Besides the color, it cleanses just fine. My skin doesn't feel dry or anything after using it. Now I'm just using this as my daily body wash until we run out, but I don't see myself going out of my way to every buy this in the future.

column6: Organic Body Scrub -Cocoa Coffee Butter -The Body Exfoliator that Heals Damaged Skin with Aloe Vera, Manuka Honey, Coconut, & Vitamins C & E For EVERY Skin Type - Hypoallergenic & Chemical Free
column13: This skeptic is a true believer
column14:
I'd like to start of by stating that I did not buy this as a medicinal product. I had already ordered this when a mosquito entered my home. I had two types of off repellent. One was in a pump bottle that I had previously used and the other an aerosol can. The pump just ran out so I used the aerosol can which my son probably almost finished. I usually say to spray our cloths, hats or supplies like sleeping bags and sheets, not our skin. I was in my home with a tank top night shirt since it's summer so I sprayed it on my hands and rubbed it on my arms and legs and broke out all over. I didn't think it was that bad at first, but it kept getting worse to the point I was ready to see a dr. I tried witch hazel, kosher activated charcoal, aloe, eucalyptus, tea tree, lavender and probably something else.

This body scrub came right on time. I figured, I tried everything else I cud think of, why not this. I washed, then applied the exfoliating scrub and let it sit on my skin for a couple of minutes. I would have left it longer, but I had an appt. to attend. To my amazement, by the end of the shower, the hives were almost even with my skin although I still itched terribly. I figured there was hope. Later in the day the itchiness lessened to the point of almost being totally gone and the hives didn't pop back up from me scratching. I never knew coffee was good for the outside of the body.

I am a skeptic and when I find something remarkable like this product and charcoal which we use for various things, I tell everyone I can about it. I'm a believer.

2016- I'm back for an update, sorry I took a while to get update. Turns out, I did react to the OFF, although there was no mosquito. The itching was stress related and the OFF brought out the hives. The continued use of the scrub and their lotion healed my skin back to normal. Of course when the stress of my son getting out of the hospital was set so I wouldn't continue to itch.

I like that because a little goes a long way and will help this bottle last much longer. I also like that it is 100% natural ingredients and mostly all aloe. column6: Lipogaine Big 3 Premium Hair Loss Prevention shampoo for Men and Women (2 in 1 formula)- 8 oz
column13: Works well on itchy scap, dandruff, and making hair look thicker
column14:
I bought this on a recommendation that it can help with hair loss. I have used it a few months so I'll describe my experience - the positive and the negative. I'm on my second bottle now. The first bottle the shampoo was thicker and this bottle (second one) the shampoo is a little more runnier. I use about a fifty cent piece / dollar piece worth of shampoo each time (I have short hair). The shampoo smells really good - a peppermint scent. It makes my hair appear thicker and my family thought it looked thicker. I believe it's too soon to say if it stopped any hair loss or regrew anything. Immediately, I noticed that I don't get any dandruff or itching. I use minoxidil and generic propecia as well. I have always had dandruff and minoxidil made my hair itch, so even if it ends up not working too well for me with preventing hair loss, I think it's worth as a dandruff cure and making my hair look thicker. None of the dandruff OTC products I used did anything for me. The price is kind of expensive, but is comparable in price to similar products. I noticed if you mess with the cap it will snap off or crack which I've never had happen with a shampoo bottle. In summary:

Positives:
- Lasts months between bottles
- Smells good
- Makes my hair look thicker
- Prevents / cures dandruff
- Prevents / cures the itch from minoxidil

Negatives:
- The product isn't the same from bottle to bottle, one bottle had thicker shampoo and one was runnier.
- The cap is very sensitive and if you tighten it too much it will crack or snap off!
- Can be pricey, but is comparable in price to the competitors (can be a positive or negative).

column6: Deodorizing Synergy Essential Oil 10 ml. 100% Pure, Undiluted, Therapeutic Grade (Blend of: Bergamot, Cypress, Lavender, Juniper, Tea Tree, Grapefruit, Patchouli and Lemon)
column14: I started my EO journey a little over 3 months ago. After attending a disappointing presentation by a rep from an mlm company. It spurred me on to do my own research. I came across Plant Therapy (PT) and choose it as my go to company for essential oils. I made this choice because they espouse safe usage (have hired one of the go to people on using EOs safety as a consultant who also developed their "kids safe" line), have trained aromatherapists on staff to answer questions, support a fabulous FB page on safe usage, etc. PT really thinks of the little touches, the EO bottles have labels on the top with the names of the oils/synergies. Trust me, it really makes it easier to find what you want/need as your collection grows. You don't have to pick up each oil and read the name. You can just glance from above. On top of that, they always offer free shipping!  While the Deodorizing Synergy can be used for making a natural deodorant, it can also be used to deodorize foul odors in a room, your shoes, gym bag, etc. Several of the EOs are antifungal, antiviral and antibacterial. It would be good to make products to sanitize different areas of the house. I might make a hand sanitizer during the winter flu season. The one caution is that the citrus oils can be phototoxic, so you need to be careful about using them on the body and then going out in the sun. I did check and all of the oils are child safe.  EDIT: Felt that I needed to edit this post. Facebook has a lot of EO groups. A frequent topic of conversation is "off label" uses of the oils. Last night, my 8 1/2 year old grandson was over after a hard day at summer camp:) He's all boy, so I'm sure it's a quite active day. He complained that he didn't feel well. Thought he had a temperature and only ate 1/2 his dinner. Wasn't interested in the "snacks" his father bought, which is unusual. He couldn't pinpoint exactly what was wrong. His head didn't feel right. I don't have any children's OTC meds around the house. Because I have cats and parrots, I don't diffuse. Thought a personal inhaler might be just the thing for him. Since I had just done the review on the Deodorizing Synergy, I thought the oils in it might be good for this purpose. I do have the 6 bottle Kids Safe Set from PT, so I reviewed the information to see if there was something for him there. I had him sniff the Deodorizing Synergy, waited about 10 minutes and asked him how he felt. He said, "About 20% better." A few minutes after that, I had him sniff Germ Destroyer, waited a few minutes and asked him which he preferred. He liked the Deodorizing Synergy better. So, I made him a personal inhaler--calling it "Feel Better!" When he was leaving, I asked him if he wanted to take it home. He gave me a resounding, "YES!"  Plant Therapy is in process of changing their labels to reflect if they are child safe. Because of that, I received this product at a discount for an honest review.

column6: Manic Panic - Pretty Flamingo Cream Hair Color
column14:
Ok, so this is a shocker. Meaning, if you dye your hair this color, be prepared for stares. If done correctly, it is the exact color you see. Depending on the length of time and hair, it may come out lighter or brighter.
If your hair is already blonde, my suggestion is, don't bleach it before you put this own. But it'd your hair is brown, red or black, bleaching is a must.
And if you have sensitive skin, I'd also suggest mixing 2 sweet n low packets in with the bleach.
For best results, I'd go with the maniac panics bleaching agent.
But please know, not everyone will get the same result. If you want pink hair and don't want to go to a salon, you're going to have to experiment a little to get the exact color you want. That goes for any hair dye, not just this. I've been using maniac panic's products for years and I've never been disappointed in what they do. Have I messed up? Yes! But it wasn't the product it was me. lol So before you buy I'd research and also maybe try temp hair dye. But if you are ready for this color, this is the brand I'd say to get.

column6: OLEHENRIKSEN Ole Henriksen 3 Little Wonders
column14:
I could not be happier I invested in these 3. The invigorating night gel and moisturizer are my favorites so I'll start with those.

The invigorating night gel has completely changed the texture of my once rough skin. The first time I used it, it burned a little but after that it only sometimes feels tingly. But the morning after applying it my skin feels SO good! It is smooth, even, and any blemishes that may have been forming are usually gone. LOVE love love this stuff and will purchase it for life! Tip: I use this every other night or once every 2 nights. You don't need to exfoliate every night even if it is gentle and the bottle will last you much longer.

The moisturizer is very nice and light but still hydrates perfectly. I have dry to combination skin and this is the most balancing moisturizer I've used. I also have extremely sensitive break out prone skin and this has never broke me out or irritated it. However, I do use another moisturizer by Andalou Naturals that is a fraction of the cost of this one that works almost as well, so I probably will not repurchase.

The vitamin c serum is nice but I have had the same results from using organic rosewater and/or organic vitamin c serum both of which are much cheaper. All of them help get rid of redness in the skin and even out your complexion as well as fight signs of aging. I won't be repurchasing this.

All in all the products are high quality and they all work well and feel AMAZING! It all depends on what you're looking for and how much you want to spend. :)

column13: Watching television even became annoying after an hour or so
column14: I am 68 years old.  Earlier this year my eye doctor observed that he could only correct my vision to 20/40.  He apparently could not see cataracts so he dialated my eyes.  At that point he was able to see them.  He told me that I should probably have surgery in the next year or so.  After several months my eyes frequently become irritated.  My vision lacked clarity at long distances while driving.  Watching television even became annoying after an hour or so.  The eye doctor told me that I do not have glaucoma, my maculas are 20/20, and I am not diabetic.  Also, he said that there is no evidence that I have ever had a stroke.  So, it was a perfect visit to the doctor except for the cataracts.  My Vision Clarity arrived in the mail yesterday morning.  I used it twice yesterday and once this morning.  Amazing!!!  I know that results from the medication are not obtained in 48 hours; but, I had immediate results.  No more eye strain.  No more eye fatigue. Clear vision at all distances.  I feel like I'm back at 20/20 or close to it. I guess I really needed these eye drops.  Regular eye drops did nothing for me.  I had tried them all.  I won't know anything about the impact upon the cataracts for many months of course.  I sure can see better!  Immediate and observable effect.

column13: BEWARE -- WILL CAUSE ULCERS & LOSS OF TASTE
column14:
Just a little preamble: I never write reviews, and I am not one of those people who likes to rant on the Internet. But any potential buyer of this product should know what they are in for.

I picked this mouthwash up on a whim at my local drugstore. It looked more professional and perhaps gentler than classic alcohol-based mouthwashes.

The first time I used the mouthwash, the sensation was so odd I almost threw it away right then. It foamed somewhat and my tongue felt very weird, like it had been badly burned and numbed at the same time. However, I continued using.

After a few days, I started developing small ulcers on the inside of my upper lip, along the gums. In an attempt to remedy this, I began using the mouthwash twice a day to clean the sores from infection.

A few days later, the ulcers were still there and suddenly I couldn't taste anything, not spicier foods. Frustrated, I continued my oral care with this product.

A few days more (about a week after buying the mouthwash), I still have ulcers all along my upper lip and am now getting additional sore along my lower gums on one side. The ulcers are so painful that eating, drinking, and even talking are all excruciating!! I have had stress-related ulcers before, but never to this extent or for this long.

Finally, it occurred to me that the only change I had made was this new mouthwash. So, I googled the brand and alas, it appears that many, many people have reported similar side effects, with some reports going back at least 5 years. Just a quick google search will show you how many people are experiencing my same symptoms as well as scarier ones: brown teeth, black gums, neck and chest pain.

Procter & Gamble are aware of the problem, but continue to sell the product with no warning. Save yourself some money and a lot of pain by passing on this mouthwash. I wish I had never picked it up myself.
