column6: AXE Total Fresh 3 in 1 Shampoo, Conditioner and Body Wash, Total Fresh 22 oz
column13: Get in, get out, get on with it
column14:
Not only is this product a shampoo, conditioner and body wash all in one but it is a microcosm example of the difference between men and women. A woman (me) wants a different product targeted for each specific need. For example, the moisturizer I'd use on my face would never be the same one I'd use on my hands. In fact, I might even have multiple products for different areas of my face! In contrast, a man (my husband) would without hesitation, use a bar of deodorant soap to wash his hair if the shampoo bottle was empty.

Axe clearly knows their target audience with this 3 in 1 product. If your man can get past the brilliant blue color, he will surely appreciate the "one stop shopping" convenience this provides. For me, though it did get both my hair and skin clean, I don't see it replacing separate shampoos and soaps I have gotten used to over a lifetime of social conditioning and media marketing. For many guys though this will be one of those "why didn't they think of this years ago" products. I see this being a gym bag and travel kit staple of every guy in America.

column6: The Blades Grim Gold Luxury Shaving Soap, \Smolder\""
column13: Beautiful Design and a Warm, Sweet Smell make this a Unique Gift
column14:
A lot of thought went into making this product, from the clever name to the cool oh-so-manly art design of the Grim Reaper, to the beautiful old, crumbly paper that carefully envelops the soap like a withered rose upon opening. I love the fact that this shaving soap comes in its own tin (not all soaps do), making it easy to store and saving me the trouble of having to find a tin in which it will fit.

Then there's the ambiguous scent. I personally wouldn't describe it as very "masculine", as others have. It's very perfumy; very impressive, yes, but it reminds me of Thierry Mugler's Angel perfume (must be the vanilla and tonka notes found in both), and, like Angel, it has the potential of being "too much" sweet after awhile. But I do enjoy it. I have to break the habit of rubbing my beard and smelling my hand in public. A female friend of mine nearly fainted when she smelled it; she LOVED it! It's the kind of smell that gets a "Ooooh!" out of anyone, so at the very least it'll make a great gift for anyone with a brush, because it's worth trying at least once.

However, I recommend this scent especially for people in cold climates. It's very warm and sweet, and for someone like me who lives in the tropics, it's a bit unpleasant with the heat.

As to the shave itself, I would give it 4 stars but I confess I am not an expert on the subject of lathering and have only tried a few other brands like Ogallala, with which I guess it compares nicely. I have no complaints with regard to functionality, and the ingredients are natural and wonderful.

column6: ArtNaturals Organic Aloe Vera Gel - for Face, Hair and Body - 100% Pure Natural and Cold Pressed - for Sun Burn, Eczema, Bug or Insect Bites, Dry Damaged Aging skin, Razor Bumps and Acne - 12 oz.
column14:
I have finally found what I am looking for!! This Aloe Vera Gel is fantastic! I have purchased a few different kinds to find one that works for my needs. This is it!

I use Aloe Vera for many things. My main use is for sunburns but it is really much, much more. Dry skin, scratches, razor burn, eczema and more! I purchased this bottle to use with my my essential oils. Essential oils that are applied to the skin need to be diluted. Usually a carrier oil is used. I find most oils too greasy wanted another option . Some recipes call for Aloe Vera so I decided to give it a try. I used 3 drops of oil to about 5 ml of Aloe Vera. Make sure you look up a dilution chart to figure out how much oil you should add. (it depends on the age of the person using it and the type of oil). I mixed a synergy of oils to help increase energy with my Aloe Vera gel and used it as you would use a lotion (applying to arms and legs). The gel does not leave a sticky or greasy feel and the smell of the oils are not overpowered by the natural smell of the gel.

Do you want to bring more natural products into your home? Need a natural bug repellent, face toner, lotion, sleep aid, acne wash? Use this product with a pure grade essential oil to help get your family away from harsh chemicals.

I am hooked. I am glad that I finally found a great natural Aloe Vera Gel.

If you found anything helpful in my review please hit "yes" to 'is this review helpful?'. I enjoy sharing what I have learned and giving my honest opinion about the items I receive from Amazon. Thank you!

column14:
I have been really impressed with this BB Cream and makeup primer. I love that this is a primer and a moisturizer because it saves me a step without having to put one of each on my face. I also love that is has anti-aging ingredients in it. I do use a vitamin C serum first and then after it's dry, I use this BB Cream for my moisturizer/primer. It makes my skin feel so smooth and my powder foundation goes nicely onto my skin. I am really happy with how this BB cream helps my foundation stay on my face all day long. I used to reapply my powder foundation at least once a day, but with using this BB Cream/primer, I never have to reapply my foundation. It quickly absorbed into my skin and didn't feel heavy or greasy. I am so impressed with how it makes my makeup look better on my face. This BB cream has replaced my other daytime moisturizers. I have sensitive skin and I had no problems after using this BB Cream for a couple weeks. I highly recommend this Glowzone BB Cream - Best Anti Aging Moisturizing Cream and Makeup Primer.

column6: Fresh Balls Lotion for Men, 3.4 fl oz
column13: Trying to tame the swamp? Look elsewhere
column14: I've been trying to find the perfect solution for "swamp crotch" and this was recommended by a few friends and some blogs. Out of all the products I've tried, this one works, but just ok. It helps to prevent the wetness and odor associated with "swamp crotch" to a degree, but doesn't do as well as other solutions. The cool thing about Fresh Balls is that even though it goes on as a lotion, if you allow ample time, it dries to provide protection. Sometimes it takes longer to dry than others, but I think that has a lot to do with how much lotion one applies to his nether-bits. I found if I put skivvies on before the lotion had dried completely, Fresh Balls didn't work nearly as well as when I would wait for the full drying effect to take place. I normally applied just after my shower and sometimes the humidity in the room made it hard to decide whether the lotion had sufficiently dried. What I didn't like was how well Fresh Balls did or didn't work. I expected to stay fresh, but the swamp was still there at the end of the day, though at a "cleaner swamp" level. My biggest problem with Fresh Balls is that by the end of the day, the Swamp Monster was mixing a pancake batter that tended to collect in the nooks and cranniesof the region. I had to shower just to feel clean, which defeats the purpose of using something to feel clean. Admittedly I live and work in a hot, humid environment, but I was looking for something to keep me dry, comfortable, and clean. Fresh Balls doesn't cut it for me, and didn't live up to the promise implied by its name. The search for truly fresh balls does not end with Fresh Balls. My favorite so far is Gold Bond spray, and until I find something better, I'll keep some on hand. At this point, I'll probably only use Fresh Balls for applications before working out or other times when I want to stay somewhat fresh and know I'll be taking a shower shortly thereafter to clean the goop.

column14: [[VIDEOID:c1fbc44455c13bbcaa062fcdf26d35d3]]Easy Face's Sonic Face Cleaning Brush Rechargeable Silicone Skin Care Facial Cleansing Brush is my first facial cleansing brush so I wasn't sure what to expect from this item. I had a vision in mind of what it would do and when it didn't do that, I wasn't sure if it worked well. I continued to use it and asked a lot of questions about it and I must say that I really love this item. I pride myself on taking really good care of my face and skin, I don't wear foundation or heavy makeup on a daily basis so I didn't think this brush could really make my skin feel or look better. Boy was I wrong! I don't know how it does it but after cleansing with this brush, I get the feeling that I've had a very expensive facial. My skin feels amazing--it feels fresh, rejuvenated, and I can't stop touching it after.  If you are looking for something that will suds up your product, this may not be the product for you as that's what I was looking for. That being said, if you want something that will make your skin feel great and look great, Easy Face's Sonic Cleaning Brush is for you. My skin actually glowed after a few days of using it. I've been under the weather and looking a bit sallow but after using this brush, I looked radiant.  I wet my face, apply my cleansing product (do not use an exfoliating cleanser or mud with this device), lather it up, and then I start to use the Sonic Brush. I'm not sure where or how but my product starts to disappear as the brush massages my face. It's very easy to hold and contours well in my hand. There are different massaging intensity levels and different levels recommended for different areas of your face. Once I've completed the cleansing/massaging action, I rinse my face and it really feels like I paid $100 for a facial.  The Sonic Cleaning Brush charges by an electrical outlet cord and once charged, it can be used cordless. I've charged mine and used it several times without recharging. The brush is not abrasive on the skin and I haven't had any type of irritation which is a HUGE plus since I have very sensitive skin. As I go along and use it more, I will update my review. I received this product free in exchange for an honest and unbiased review. This review is my own opinion and what I truly thought of this item.

column13: I don't usually write reviews but...

I was initially in the hunt for organic toothpaste as I'm mindful of all the chemicals in toothpaste. I stumbled on this, and due to good reviews decided to purchase. Boy was I pleasantly surprised! I loved the packaging and the handwritten note was also a nice touch.
Lately I have been sad about my tea/coffee stains, but cannot withstand the grossness of teeth whiteners, plus they make my teeth severely sensitive for months. And the thought that I'm chipping away at my enamel in doing so also bothered me.
SO, not only did this clean my teeth very well, but it also truly did WHITEN them!
Now, I've used plain activated charcoal before, and it's incredibly messy (sticks and won't come off), however I found this formula easy to rise off.
Another note: I have had a one sensitive tooth for a while now and this stuff within a matter of days took it completely away. I honestly didn't believe the reviews completely upon reading them, but now I can attest to them.
So now my husband and I have clean white teeth! And he usually prefers to stick to what he knows, however he's been strictly using this since the results are that good.
I hope they never stop making it.

column6: Almay Oil-Free Eye Makeup Remover Pads
column14: I have sensitive eyes, wear contacts, and only use waterproof mascara and eyeliner.  I have tried many waterproof makeup removers (both high and low end).  They have irritated my eyes, clogged my tear ducts, given me styes, and broken my lashes with the scrubbing.  While this eye makeup remover is not perfect, it is the best that I have found.  I'm happy enough with it that I am done searching.  I no longer own 3-4 eye makeup removers at any given time.  Now, it's just this one.  It is also one of the very few eye makeup removers I have found that is tested by both dermatologists and opthalmologists.  It will completely remove all eye makeup, but you need to follow the directions and be patient.  After generously moistening a cotton pad with the remover, I press the pad to my eyelashes and leave it there for 30 seconds.  At this point my mascara is now loose and gentle wiping will remove the rest.  After removing my face makeup and eye makeup I use Purpose Gentle Cleanser (my dermatologist got me hooked) on my face and eyelids for a final wash to remove any remaining residue from my cleansers.  Purpose will not burn the eyes, but it also will not remove waterproof makeup on its own.

column6: Philips Norelco QG3280 Multigroom Pro
column14:
I had this unit for a little over 2 years before it just went dead. Keep in mind I have very fair hair and I shave maybe 2 times per week for my face and maybe one time a month for the rest of my body. I used it primarily in the shower and one day it was just dead. After it went dead, I noticed there were hairline cracks in the plastic casing and I never dropped it or abused it. I also cleaned and oiled it after almost every use. The cracks stemmed down the back from where the attachments go (on the side opposite to the "On" switch), through the push mechanism (that is the lock for lengthening attachments), and beyond almost to the center of the unit's body. So, I would guess some water finally made it inside this unit to end it's life.

So, now I'm stuck overseas for the next four months with no shaver. It's not the end of the world, but razors give me pimples and ingrown hairs. I purchased this unit mainly because it was one of a few that advertised 100V-240V. Anyway, I'll be looking at other brands that are maybe built a little better. This is the first unit I've had that died prematurely for something other than a battery issue. Then again, this is the first unit I've had that was "waterproof." So, it might still be working if water wasn't a factor.

column6: eb5 Intense Moisture Anti-Aging Cream
column14:
Before I talk about my experience with this product, I'd like to describe my skin because I believe that each person's individual body chemistry impacts how well a product works for them. I am 50 years old. My skin is thin and fair. It is not especially sensitive to any particular chemical or products, but there have been rare occasions where my skin is left dry or itchy with certain treatments (though this is rare). My main issues are a lot of fine lines around my eyes, deep wrinkles running from my nose to my mouth, and various lesser wrinkles running across my forehead. My normal routine for facial moisturizers is to apply a Vitamin C serum then a moisturizer of some kind. I rotate products to give my skin a different experience. However, for the purpose of assessing a new product, I stop using all products except the tested one (so I only used this one during my assessment phase - no vitamin C, no other moisturizer). I wash my face with regular Ivory soap which tends to leave it dry and tight. I have a lot of experience from which to gauge the effectiveness of this product relative to others, but only with my particular skin type.

I applied this as directed twice a day - at night after a shower and again in the morning. The difference between this and my usual moisturizers was immediate in terms of appearance. Lines were definitely less visible, especially around my eyes. It didn't give me a tight Botox-like line-free face nor did it make me look 25 again, but it definitely diminished lines and plumped skin. I was impressed with the results.

Using this product is very different from other applications because it is super thick and concentrated. I used it for nearly a week based on what stuck to the insert in the lid. You should use it very sparingly for best results given that it has mineral oil in it. Also, the product will last a very long time that way and you really don't need more. I dotted it on my skin in a regularly spaced fashion then rubbed it in. This left my skin smooth and soft, but not oily or greasy at all. It's fully absorbed within 10 minutes.

At the time of this review, the price for a 4-oz. jar is around $28. With what I'd deem "proper" use (sparing), I think this could last a year and is actually a very economical addition to a moisturizing routine. I've used a lot of very good products for skin care. This is definitely one that I'd add to that list.hen rubbed it in. This left my skin smooth and soft, but not oily or greasy at all. It's fully absorbed within 10 minutes.

I know that subjective bit of information doesn't help, but this is something you can't really tell the benefits of unless you can check your blood daily. Strangely, I have noticed the hair thickening effect of this stuff (not just on the head). So that does tell me it's doing something and I'm pretty much satisfied with that. The old Toco-8 and a rival brands gel capsule based product just weren't as effective as this.
Take it (like I do) with a good vitamin, fish oil, lecithin, good fat, and your joint support stuff, and you'll feel like it only helps the others.

If heart health and hair are on your list of concerns (I know it is on mine), you can't really do much better than taking this.

column14: I bought this product based on it being one of Amazon's #1 best sellers. It's a good entrance to wet shaving at a reasonable cost. However, I do like the Merkur 34c better because it has a more traditional (shorter) length handle, which makes it easier for me to shave with. With wet shaving, you're suppose to let the weight of the razor do the shaving (holding the razor with only a few fingers at the very bottom of the razor handle) and not apply additional pressure. However, I find the longer handle makes me want to use this like a cartridge razor. I just don't see the need for the extra length of this handle, but I'm extremely happy it introduced me to wet shaving with a double edge safety razor. Much closer shave that with a cartridge razor for a fraction of the cost!

It does what it claims. I have corse thick curly/wavy frizzy color treated asian hair and this thing works great on my hair, so far I used only 2 times. Although, you shouldn't be expecting pin straight hair with this tool, however this will make your hair look naturally straight (little bit of texture/wave) and little of puff sexiness in a nicer way. I used to use straightener and I personally don't like pin straight hair, because it weights my hair down and my roots will ended up become really flat. Also, I used to spend 45min to 90min to straighten my hair with straightener, but with this brush at most 20min.
After using it 2 times, I'm achieving the look that I've always wanted, which is straight yet careless looking hair with a bit of volume and body in the roots.
I agree that it may make your hair look a bit dry after use, but I noticed on my hair it will go away after 20min, or if I'm in a rush then I rub in some hair serum after styling.
The only cons is that max heat is 450‚Ñâ, still a little lower for my asian hair. I think if it was 500‚Ñâ would have been much better. But it still works really good.

column6: Tea Tree Oil (Australian) 4 Fl.oz. with Glass Dropper 100 % Pure and Natural Therapeutic Essential Oil to Help in Fighting Dandruff, Acne, Toenail Fungus, Yeast Infections, Cold Sores & More...
column13: NEVER RUN OUT OF TEA TREE OIL !!
column14:
Never run out of tea tree oil. Its like milk, bread, shampoo and every other item you would notice if you didn't have it. If you've never used it.. Or even read about it, you don't know what your missing.. But you should.. Like I say with all the other reviews I do. I'm not going to spout off the same stuff you read above.. I, myself, just learned about this last year, when my granddaughter brought lice (YEAHHH LICE!!!) I had a nightmare with lice when my own kids when they were in grade school.. Due to one family member not wanting to bother with the shampooing, washing, etc, we had them for a freaking MONTH!! After spending hundreds of dollars and hours and hours of shampooing, washing, picking ( One 4 hour pick-fest put me in the hospital when my back went out) and fogging, I finally learned that in addition to one of the kids bringing them back in, the others could be getting resistant to the medication (even the prescriptions). I started researching and learned about Mayonnaise.. That did the trick, but I tortured my kids with sleeping with shower caps and greasy handfuls of it on the livingroom floor for 4 days... I was done playing!!! I was just done!! years later, my granddaughter is living with us.. Thank God I have blood that repels mosquitos, fleas, lice, etc, but I have a daughter that is like honey to them.. This time after searching I learned about coconut oil and tea tree oil. I have stocked up and have multiple brands an types of both.. I haven't seen anything, besides Aloe Vera, that has so many uses.. If something is causing illness, insects of other issues, if you have Tea Tree, Aloe or coconut around, chances are your going to be good.. The dropper on mine was broken when I got this batch, but I'm positive it was after, because it was bubble wrapped and shattered in one place as if someone crunched it.. Luckily I'm so used to using this, I no longer bother with a dropper.. This stuff it like gold..

column13: Dry, sensitive skin?  This one is worth a try for sure!  Especially if you are a fan of lavender :)
column14:
My skin is VERY dry and VERY sensitive so it's a struggle trying to find products that provide enough hydration while not creating a reaction on my fussy skin! This lotion is AMAZING! A true lavender smell that lasts on your skin...unlike some lavender lotions that have a funky, fake smell.
You can tell this is a qualtiy lotion when you first apply it to your skin. It takes very little to hydrate and absorbs quickly. Normally, as dry as my skin is, I typically need to apply 3 or 4 coats of lotion. This lotion only requires one application which really shocked me!
The ONLY drawback for me is the price. Yes, it's worth it for sure but I'm careful how I use it to make it lasts as long as possible.
You can watch Dr. Bonner's website for monthly specials as this lotion pops up once in awhile for a discount. Otherwise, Amazon's price is competitive on this.

column6: The Wet Brush Pro Select, Black
column14: I have a mane. People who say they have a mane, haven't met me. It's pretty manely. Seriously when I get highlights, people take 20 minutes trying to detangle my hair. Then when they dry it, it tangles again. My hair is thick. My hair is course. My hair is the worst. It is damaged. But this thing makes it MANAGEABLE. Seriously I used to dread combing through my hair after showers. Now it's not as terrible. This helps so so much without making me wince with every brush stroke. I have to say because I have such thick hair I definitely have a TON of hair in the brush after, but I've decided it is hair that my other brush is missing, and it's the hair that would have shed all over me throughout the day. So thanks, brush, for saving me that annoying feeling of hair on the back of my arm all day long. I like to use this on my wet hair when I get out, usually starting at the ends and working my way up. Then I use it as a paddle brush to blow my hair dry. It doesn't pull on my hair when I blow dry, it keeps my hair from getting matted and tangled, and I will never live without one again. The reason for 4 stars instead of 5 is I'm saving the 5 star for a product that does not even pull my hair at all. This doesn't hurt when it pulls, but I have a mane, so obviously it's going to pull. Hope this is helpful! The picture is my hair after using the brush to blow dry and straighten.

column13: Great tool to have if you have thick stubborn callus on your feet.
column14: I had a callus build up on my foot and regular methods and attempts to remove it with a grinder just were not cutting it ... no pun intended. This worked very well at removing the callus by shaving it down then using the other end to smooth it out. The way the blade is mounted makes it safer so you don't accidentally cut yourself but you should still be cautious becuase I can see how it would be possible to cut yourself if your not careful. The handle and angle of the blade helps reach the bottom of your foot easier and it has a protective cover that slides back and forth and snaps into place so you can switch back and forth from using the blade or the "cheese grater". The only reason I did not give it a five star review is becuase I wish it came with a few extra blades, so you will want to purchase those as well becuase they get dull pretty fast. The other reason is that the other end that I refer to as the "cheese grater" is a thin piece of metal that is curved and snaps/slides into place on the handle and has fallen out a couple times during use. It easily snaps/slides back on and still works well to smooth out the callus.

column6: Elite Serum Rx is the Best Anti Aging Serum for Wrinkles, Bags, and Dark Circles | Best Eye Serum with Argireline
column13: Firm Believer in this Firming Serum
column14: After researching methods to reduce eye puffiness, I found the website for this serum and was impressed with the innovative ingredients. The active ingredient-Argireline, has recently been developed and tested, to reduce wrinkles and signs of aging around the eyes. Unlike Botox, this Serum does not require painful injections, which I have always been apprehensive about.  Another bonus,  is that the ingredients are non-comedogenic, which means that it is safe for sensitive skin. The fact that it is Oil-Free, ensures that it will not clog pores and exacerbate irritated or acne prone skin. Being an avid Amazon Bargain Hunter, I was very pleased to find this product on here. In contrast to similar anti-aging skin creams, this serum seems to be on the expensive side. But after doing an ingredient comparison, the obvious difference between this serum and generic eye creams, is the quality and potency. You do not need to use a generous amount of cream to achieve outstanding results. Specifically, I started off with using a pea-sized amount under my eyes, where I experience frequent puffiness, at night. After repeating this routine for a few nights, every morning I could visibly see a gradual difference, as far as an improvement in the appearance of my under-eye bags. Truthfully, the results are not overnight or drastic, as many similar gimmick anti-aging products make false claims about. As with anything, to reap the full benefits, I have added this serum to my nightly skin care regimen and will continue using on a daily basis. So far, I have not experienced any side effects or skin irritation from this product, which makes it all the more worthwhile.

column6: Green Tidings All Natural Deodorant, Extra Strength All Day Protection; 2 Sizes; Unscented or Lavender (Vegan, Certified Cruelty Free)
column14:
It is day two on this new deodorant and I have to say I am pleasantly surprised. I have been using the clinical drugstore deodorants for about two years now - not because of sweat but because I feel I stink a little - especially when I am wearing a tank top or sleeveless dress (tshirts or blouses sometimes) I am not sure if anyone else notices it but I feel uncomfortable. I have noticed a pattern but maybe it also attributes to the type of fabric as well (i.e. breath ability).

Anyway, so I saw the great reviews and decided to buy it. I have sensitive skin and so far no issues with rashes, dry skin etc. I use about 3 swipes in the morning and also give it a quick rub in with my fingers to make sure my underarm is well coated. I haven't noticed any unusual sweating yet, but like another reader, I keep sniffing my underarms - and it doesn't smell! I may try a sleeveless top next - this will be the ultimate test.

The leaflet that comes with the brochure should have instructions on how to use the deodorant. Although it appears to work like a normal deodorant stick, I needed to re-read the Amazon description on how to use it and what to expect (i.e. when first applied underarm may be sticky or do you put it on dry or wet underarms, do you use in the morning and night etc.). I would rather this than the section (s) on posting a review on Amazon if I am happy with the product as these days it's an almost given.

column13: Leaves skin feeling so clean, smooth, and soft - great face wash!
column14:
I have been using this product for close to a month now, and my face feels great. My skin feels so clean and smooth every time I use it, I love it! I have normal skin, not too dry, not oily, and no acne, so I cannot vouch for how it would handle any of those types of skin, however it feels so natural and easy on the skin, that I imagine it would work wonders on any of them.

I don't know how else to describe this cleanser other than it feels simple and pure; it is so mild, there is nothing in it that irritates my skin, or any of my senses, for that matter. It doesn't have a fragrance (which bother me immensely) and my skin just feels so simply clean from using this product.

I use it in conjunction with its microdermabrasion counterpart, and I have noticed quite a difference in the last few weeks in how smooth and soft the skin on my face is. Very happy with it!

column6: Remington PF7500 F5 Comfort Series Foil Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver
column13: Guess I'm not an electric guy
column14:
I've used razors for 25 years and never used an electric, so I'm aware that I'm a newbie when it comes to electrics. So consider that when reading the review. That said, I wasn't impressed and I think I'll stick to razors.

I feel I gave it a fair shot. I tried using it for a week. Read the manual, read articles online and watched a couple videos on how to use an electric. I felt it took too long to get anything resembling a close shave. The shave was definitely not as close as a razor and I never could quite figure out how to completely shave the area under my chin. Granted, with practice I'm sure it'd get easier and faster, but I don't see the benefit. It's not going to be faster or easier than what I currently do ( I shave in the shower, which makes for a pretty fast, close shave.) and it's not going to be as close.

However, for non-facial hair (under arm and whatnot), I did find it to be easier than a razor. In that case, I'm just trimming and I don't care if it's a super close shave or perfect. So I will be using it for that purpose.

So this is really a 3.5 star review. three stars because I think it's a good product that just didn't work for me for the stated purpose. (If you like electric shavers and have used them for years, this is review is probably not going to be useful to you) And plus 1/2 a star for being useful for body hair.

column6: Braun
column13: Braun Pulsonic shavers are OVER-ENGINEERED with too many tiny breakage-prone parts
column14: I replaced an older Braun 7505 shaver (with sideburn trimmer) with an OUTRAGEOUSLY EXPENSIVE Braun Series 7 (790 cc) Pulsonic shaver and cleaning system that has a liquid-crystal display and LEDs.  The Pulsonic definitely moves much faster, but ‚Ä¶ Unfortunately, after a little over a year and a half the tiny plastic and nylon parts in the sideburn trimmer catastrophically failed leaving a couple of flapping plastic sliders.  After about two years, the center cutting head for longer whiskers failed catastrophically in a shower of tiny parts.  So now I have a Pulsonic that only shaves very short whiskers and does not trim sideburns.  I still have the old 7505 which is perfectly fine, but slower, that I use for trimming sideburns and shaving after more than 2-3 days.  I then finish with the Pulsonic. The old 7505 is a nice straight-forward design but is slower.  It would have been great to have the Pulsonic motor built within the simpler and solid design of the 7505.  One wonders what possesses the Braun designers and engineers to come up with those ridiculously over-engineered and complex shavers that are so failure prone.  I had a suspicion that the sideburn trimmer on the Pulsonic was going to fail when I first saw how it works because it was obviously laughably and stupidly complex.  Hey Braun designers & engineers ‚Ä¶ WAKE UP and design for longevity!

column13: Great quality Closed Comb Safety Razor
column14:
August 11, 2015
Good razor, kind of mild but gets the job done

August 21st, 2016
Its been a year since I have been using a safety razor and have been pretty good with it. First off when I did order this my first order was lost, but amazon was able to send me a replacement. I use to use some other cheaply made double edge razors but I did my research and found this brand is good one to buy.
Pros
- Build quality is top notch. I have been rotating this with my Gillette 1975 razor. The chrome plate is good no discoloration yet.
- Its closed combed. I like closed comb razors because your less likely to nick your self but if I get lazy and forget to shave I usually use my slant razor. Everything screws in perfectly. It doesn't wobble or get loose while shaving
- The black handle really makes this razor attractive and at first I though this would be slippery but I had no problem doing three passes with a wet hand.

Cons
I cant really find any cons but I would of liked it if they use Nickel instead but its fine.

I will continue to update this. I will update my experience again next year.

Overall this a great quality safety razor and will continue to use with my Gillette Safety Razor. Would a recommend? Yes I would, this is a great razor and you wont regret it!

Thank you for reading!

column6: Remington PF7400 F4 Comfort Series Foil Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver, Black
column13: Can't Go Wrong For The Price
column14:
The Remington PF7400 is a really good basic electric shaver. It does not have all the "bells and whistles" of some of the more expensive models on the market, but at a $40 price point, it is a great starter or introduction/budget electric shaver. It also makes a great travel shaver since you will not be worried about losing it or damaging your "favorite" high-end device.

Provides a good, clean, smooth shave. Not as "fast" as a blade, but it gets the job done effectively. Did not notice any "pinching" or "hair pulling" with this model (as others are prone to do). The battery life is about average and what you would expect from this price point, but honestly I typically just keep the cord attached to mine so that I never have to worry about power loss or "slow down." Ergonomic grip and shaver head. Reaches all the areas you should need to reach without worry.

Bodybuilders: I would not use this as a body shaver simply for time and power, you might be better off looking into another device or product.

Four solid stars. Nothing wrong with this product, but nothing outstanding either. Well above average though. Can't really go wrong for the price.

column6: John Frieda Colour Refreshing Gloss, Black, 6 Ounce
column13: Helped with brassiness and made hair soft and manageable!
column14:
My hair before gloss application:
I purchased this gloss in "Cool Brown" to help tone my brassy ombred hair. The medium brown part of my hair has gotten slightly red/brown and the dark blonde part has a tinge of orange. I decided to forgo with redyeing/touching up my hair since summer is a notorious season to turn people's locks brassy as hell. I decided to just let my hair grow out since I didn't have a noticeable line of demarcation and the faded dye blends fairly well to my natural hair color.

Hair condition after gloss application:
I must say that I'm impressed. The gloss made a difference after just one use. My hair became soft, manageable, and less frizzy. I noticed that the gloss tinted some of the brassiness away. The dyed medium brown got slightly darker and the dark blonde is less orange. I deducted a star because even though the gloss made my hair soft, my hair wasn't any shinier than before.

Even though 'shiny hair' wasn't checked off my list during the first use, I would imagine that the gloss would work much better after several uses. I'm actually pretty happy with my first experience that I purchased 2 more since amazon is selling the gloss for less(at that time) than any other stores.

column6: Conair 1875 Watt Cord Keeper 2-in-1 Hair Dryer, Black
column13: So quiet, your kids (likely) won't run screaming!
column14:
Two things I love most about this dryer: The color and the retractable cord.

Other good points: It is very quiet, but in my brain, because it is quiet it isn't doing as good of a job. My daughter would run from the sound of the previous dryer. This one she tolerates enough to allow me to dry her bangs before she runs away. The amount of air is much less than my previous dryer, but my old dryer was, well, old. There is no medium speed, it is high or low. There are three temp settings, plus the cool shot.

I have not noticed a difference in dry time for my hair. But my hair is VERY thick and usually doesn't dry for four to five hours (underneath) if I towel dry and go. My hair is only chin length, so that is a lot of drying time. With this dryer, to get my hair almost dry, (approx 85%,) it takes 10-15 minutes, not much difference than my old dryer. But, I can tell this one isn't frying my hair. I asked my hair dresser if the ceramic tourmaline thing was a big deal or just impressive advertising. She said it provides a very big difference in dry time and keeping healthy hair. No false advertising in her opinion!

So, while I like it, I gave it four stars because the drying time is the same. Other than that, this is a pretty great dryer!

column6: Ocean Potion Anti-Aging Sunblock Lotion SPF 50-8 oz
column14: LOVE this product. I started using this sunscreen several years ago (back when it came in a purple bottle; there was a light blue one that I liked as well) because it actually doesn't smell like sunscreen; this one smells a lot like orange creamcicle. It also has a very light, fresh feeling going on, unlike many other sunscreens. I have also used Neutrogena's ultra sheer sunscreen and can say that despite the claims on the bottle, Neutrogena is considerably greasier than Ocean Potion. I also think that because of the lighter texture, it's easier to get ample coverage with Ocean Potion; as a result, I have gotten sunburned less often with Ocean Potion than with Neutrogena. My only complaint is that at the end of the day if I rub my skin, grimy gray stuff rubs off -- like a combination of dead skin and sunscreen. Haven't noticed this with other brands (Neutrogena, Aveeno) but I think the pros far outweigh this one con. Can't find this product in stores where I live, so I've started buying it online; absolutely worth it.

column13: Cigar:Quite possibly the greatest tobacco cologne!
column14: There have been quite a few tobacco based cologne's that have came along and gone (in some cases) and none of them have full focus on the word "tobacco" in craftsmanship as you'd think.Lapidus is awfully floral and unusually fruity.Witness by Jacques Bogart's use of cinnamon was good but sweetly and reminded me of a cinnamon pipe tobacco...still good though.Havana by Aramis is great but clove is an occasional appreciation.Cigar by Remy Latour reminds me more of both a cigar and pipe tobacco character yet nothing about it smells out of place.It's smoothly sweet and very animalic musky.Woody with sandalwood and cedar reminds you of a cigar box.Patchouli does add a little green earthiness that enriches the musk and wood.Imagine your walking through the mall of the 70s and 80s pre public smoking enforcement era.The thick cigar smoke cloud billowing from the smoke shop selling chess boards of all kinds.As you walk along an elderly gentlemen puffing a tasty aromatic from his pipe and it all marries together.Lastly the scent of dry sandalwood and patchouli from the from the incense shop down the way and making it more woody and musky.Flat out I'll come forward and say you have to like these older notes used in colognes from past decades to appreciate Cigar.Thank goodness this excellent cologne exists because it makes me wish such a cigar could provide a taste to match this manly scent.Five Stars!

column6: Wahl Ear, Nose and Brow Trimmer #5545-400
column13: Best Nose and Ear Hair Timmer I've Owned
column14:
Every trimmer I've owned (3 prior to this one) sounded like it's gears were made of plastic and they were about to die right out of the box. So this trimmer got four stars from me just for sounding like it wasn't on it's last leg. Actually it sounds strong and power delivery is consistent - 5th star earned. Other trimmers seemed to spin slower or faster depending on the angle at which I held them! This trimmer says it can operate in the shower, but I just have this thing about not taking electrical appliances in the shower with me. I know it's a low voltage, but still not going to do it.

Pros:
Runs strong at a consistent speed and at all angles
Has 3 different attachments - Ear, Nose, Brow
Easily removable top piece for cleaning
No pulling or tearing of hair, as advertised
Good value at under $8
Reputable name - Whal. I have a Whal clipper for trimming my hair that is now 20 years old and still works great

Cons:
Plastic is a little cheap looking, but then it's less than $8
Would have been nice if they had provided a case to keep trimmer and all attachments together

Summary:
Quality brand name product that does what is says it will do (though I didn't test in water) without pinching, pulling hairs or nicking, for a really low price. I am very happy with this purchase.

column13: Wonderful natural soap that leaves you clean and no harsh chemicals!
column14: It's funny how becoming a parent suddenly shifts a lot of things that in the past may not have been so important to you, into very sharp focus.  For me, that thing was the use of chemicals and dyes in my products - particularly beauty products.  But as soon as I held my first child, I knew I needed to protect her from what I could and that meant using natural products whenever possible, including natural soap!  I received this bar of Forganica Natural bar soap in exchange for my honest opinion.  This natural soap contains no harsh or harmful chemicals, preservatives, parabens, sulfates, dyes, synthetic fragrances or other general fake "stuff".  It is also naturally fragrance-free so if someone in your house has a fragrance issue, this is perfect.  It leaves your skin feeling clean and smooth, but without leaving all the unsafe "stuff" behind - I love that.  As with other natural soaps you don't get the lather that as Americans, we've come to associate with "clean".  You still get some lather but only what would naturally occur not the extra fluff and stuff. Great soap - I really like it!

column6: BreathRx Anti-Bacterial Mouth Rinse
column13: Okay, but not great; plus it's extremely sweet
column14:
It's effective but not great (or $25 great). I would probably suggest the smaller size at first to be sure the flavor isn't overwhelming to you.

Pros:
- It is pretty effective in helping you keep a fresh breath/feeling for several hours. I'm a bit obsessed with having a clean feeling with my teeth/mouth and it accomplishes this, for the most part.
- It's an all-in-one mouthwash that doesn't require mixing 2 solutions prior to use (e.g., as SmartMouth does); so, it's a little more convenient to use when not at home.

Cons:
- It is so sweet--ridiculously strong artificial sweetener--that it borders on gross to me.
- It leaves more of an aftertaste than other brands I've tried. If I drink water even an hour or more later, I can sometimes still sense a vague odd taste of the mouthwash.
- It is quite expensive, even relative to other brands of these types of clinical/long-lasting mouthwashes.

SmartMouth is probably still my favorite among the "clinical" or long-lasting mouthwashes. Arm & Hammer Truly Radiant is also, in my opinion, really effective, especially with it being just a regular (non clinical-type) mouthwash and relatively reasonably priced.

column13: For Shinier and softer hair every time.
column14: I haven't had time to take care of my hair much. I must admit I am the type of woman who just always keeps her hair in a bun. Not because I'm lazy but my hair is just so damaged to let it let loose. I got excited when I received  this and I thought to myself it's  about time to let my hair loose. I used it after shower and only left it for about 30mins. I remember my hairstylist before who told me that when you put treatment to your hair make sure to shampoo it first for best absorption. Just shampoo no conditioner. This removes all the residue from what you used beforehand and also the dusts and dirts. It smells like a lotion and the consistency is thick. It is actually best to put a hair cap and leave it there until you're  ready to wash it. After that I just dried my hair with a fan. My hair feels so soft and I can see it's shinier. I took a picture of before and after and you can see the difference. The damage is still there but it's  starting to work. Of course I do not expect it to work that fast with just one use. I purchased this for a discounted price in exchange for my unbiased and honest review. But it's  worth it. Saves you money from going to salon to get your hair restored.

column6: BaKblade DIY Back & Body Shaver
column13: One of the best products ever invented; why didn't anybody think of this before??
column14:
I had imagined a product like this for years, hoping somebody would invent it, and today that dream came true. I had been using depilatories for awhile--Nair for Men, Veet for women--and they were gross, smelly, and burned if you didn't use them the right way, not to mention the fact that I had to look around to find the right kind of thing to apply it with, turn around to see myself in a mirror (and still get it on haphazardly) and then stand in the shower for an inordinate amount of time to get it off. Before that I went through two Mangroomers. The first one fell apart when the blade loosened, and even the replacement blades wouldn't stay on well. Same with the second one, in addition to the fact that the blades are so small that you have to keep guessing where you're hitting and how it will turn out--and you need to use it in the shower where there's no mirror, unless you want to clean hair out of the entire bathroom for about a week.

Now comes baKblade's "BIGMOUTH." I happened to search Amazon for a back hair shaver, thinking maybe somebody out there invented something, and whoa, there it was. I couldn't believe it existed, because it was just the thing I pictured somebody should invent for this headache. I ordered it and it came priority mail in a few days. This afternoon I threw my shirt off and went at it, and it worked unbelievably! First, it feels like a back scratcher as it shaves you (it works like one of those old barber's scissors with the comb/blade). It's fast, painless (actually stimulating, like a nice back rub) and gets the hair off immediately. No worries about a mirror, because the blade's wide enough to get a sense of where it's covering your back. My only recommendation is to stand in the shower when you use it, since the hair falls everywhere. It's light years beyond the Mangroomer in efficiency and ease of use (the handle's the perfect length to reach your whole back, shoulders etc. without having to see what you're doing), and it works phenomenally. Get this thing into stores--FAST!), and it works phenomenally. Get this thing into stores--FAST!

column6: LANVIN Eclat d'Arpege Eau de Parfum
column13: Real VS. Fake....I think this stuff is real
column14:
Ok, so I have read ALL the reviews and I have searched for this perfume at many different online sites, including Target. I ordered it once from Target, the package never came and they ended up canceling it and now you can't order it from Target. So, I am not sure about the fake versus real. But, I have a real bottle of this stuff at home that I purchased in the mall and I compared it to this bottle and they seem to be the same. There are few differences. For example, the cap and the nozzle are both a little bit smaller than the real bottle at home, the real bottle at home has 80% on the bottom while this bottle has 78%. Other than that, the drawings and the artwork are all the same and the barcode is on the bottom of the glass case the perfume arrived in.

The real test: I sprayed it on my arm early in the morning the other day, did many chores, ran around, washed dishes, etc, and the smell was still there when I went to shower at 11pm. I am wearing it today at work and I will continue to test it, but I think it is the real stuff. Even if it is fake, this is a good fake because it did not burn when I put it on, the smell is exactly the same and it has stayed for an all day wear. AND, the price is just right:)

column14: I have purchased two different brands of rose hip oil. I found this price to be very reasonable.  When I was able to find a discount code to purchase this at a lower price i of course jumped on the opportunity.  There are many benefits of Rosehip oil.  Since it comes specifically from only one kind of rose it makes it just a little more special.  It has great properties like Vitamin A and C and has been known to help with fine lines and wrinkles by stimulating collagen production.  It can also help reduce the appearance of scarring.  I also did research on the product to see what other benefits it held.  I found that it also can reduce UV damage already done to your skin. So many of us grew up in a time where tan was sexy.  And now we all live with a fear of the damage that is to come.  I love that this may reverse some of that and make my skin a little younger looking.  Very impressed with the size and packaging of this product as well as the quality.

column6: e.l.f. Glitter Mascara, 0.145 Fluid Ounce
column13: Tasteful sparkle over your regular mascara
column14:
I purchased this despite the other negative reviews, because I thought that it could still work fine. And in reality, it really does.

The glitter is more of an accent than painting your eyelashes silver, which isn't a bad thing. As a matter of fact, I would consider this to be more "adult" like, in a manner of speaking, because it adds a touch of glitter rather than completely silver or sparkling eyelashes.

The wand works just fine. It's a ridged wand that picks up the clear fluid with glitter. The glitter is pretty fine, and it is best to add after you have already used mascara and curled your lashes. Add this as your finishing touch. It will add a touch of sparkle to your lashes, but nothing heavy. Whatever you use as your base mascara is going to be the primary color, and this just adds a small bit of glitter. Depending on how your lighting is, you may or may not think it is noticeable. It is probably the most noticeable under "evening" type lighting.

If you want a little extra sparkle, just dab a teeny tiny bit on your eyelid where you would put eyeliner, and then blend in and let dry. That will add more sparkle if what is on your lashes isn't enough for you.

If you want solid silver, shiny eyelashes or a thick, heavy glitter, this isn't for you. However, if you want just a tasteful bit of sparkle on your regular mascara to help your eyes "pop", then this is perfect. Some days I'm just in the mood to "sparkle" a little, yet still want to act within my 40 year old timeframe, and this helps me do both. :-)

column6: Coffee Clay Cellulite Mask & Firming Cool Gel - Topical 2 Step Anti-Cellulite Treatment for Tighter Skin - Quickly Burns & Firms Thigh Fat, Belly Fat, Arm Fat
column13: This stuff is helping my skin look & feel it's best!
column14:
I have been really into Cellulite treatments and Skin Firming treatments of all kinds lately since I am trying to get beautified and looking my best for our upcoming cruise in a few weeks. While I STILL do not believe a cream, mask or any other type of topical treatment get rid of Cellulite or fat in general I DO think it can help the appearance, tone and texture of the skin. I am ALL for that!
This Coffee Clay Body Mask & Cool Gel by Jaowying Beauty really DOES help with the tone and texture of skin which makes any Cellulite look less noticeable. I apply the Coffee Clay Body Mask to my abdomen, buttocks and thighs for about 15-20 minutes (or until fully dry) and then wash off (I usually just take a shower to fully rinse it off). After I rinse off I then apply the Cool Gel which is supposed to help prevent any excess accumulation of body fat.
I can't say with 100% certainty that these products will reduce Cellulite or fat but I CAN say that they definitely help reduce the appearance of Cellulite and fat. After I use these products my skin looks and feels more firm and tone and the texture is more smooth as well.
Jaowying Beauty recommends that you use plastic wrap to achieve better results but I feel like my results were great without using the wrap. They also say if you have sensitive skin this product may not be for you but I didn't have any sensitivity issues with either product. They also recommend that you eat well and exercise to get the best results possible.
I use the Coffee Clay Body Mask & Cool Gel about 3-5 times a week to maintain the smooth and firm appearance of the skin.

***I did receive this product at a discount or complimentary in exchange for my honest, unbiased review. However, I was not paid in anyway and my thoughts and opinions are my own.***

column14:
These comments are about the lavender shampoo. I have another older bottle, more than a half full, in another bathroom. I used it to compare the labels. The wheat protein is out. Some of the other ingredients have moved up or down in the ingredient's list (meaning more or less of that ingredient is used in each bottle).

In the description, it no longer says \\\CONTAINS 70% ORGANIC CONTENT..\\\\\". This has changed to \\\\\"CONTAINS ORGANIC...\\\\\". The second line now also begins with \\\\\"NO GMO'S\\\\\" which isn't stated on the older bottle.

The only reason I decided to compare labels is because I noticed the shampoo in the new bottle I had bought was less viscous (more watery in consistency) and the lavender scent was... different. The intensity is still there, it just smells a little off.

The other reason I checked is because my hair is frizzy after using this new batch. I could go 1-2 days without using the conditioner, but now I have to use it every time I shampoo or my half my hair looks likes my head is too close to a balloon.

I know you can't please everyone (I read in a much earlier review (2012?) someone was complaining the formula had changed -they'd added wheat protein-), but I wish they had stayed with the 'old' formula."

column14: Last month I was dealing with really dry skin. It was most prominent on my eyelids. I tried all sorts of moisturizers, butters, creams, serums, lotions, and oils. Nothing worked. I had just started using this as a body scrub and decided to try it out as a face wash. I read through all of the ingredients and they were all natural and a lot of them were essential oils. I tried it and within a week my face was no longer peeling, flaking, or cracking. HooraY! I tried including a before/after picture, but my only pic that really shows my eyelid afterwards has makeup applied, but I think you can still see the difference. I couldn't even wear makeup with my dry patches. It looked terrible and hurt a lot. It is very strong though! It is definitely a concentrated formula. I just apply a little to a cotton pad and wet it. It lathers up really well and spreads easily. I have been cleaning my face nightly with it (trying to avoid the eye area). I have noticed my skin is clearer, smoother, and  not as dry. I love it. I received a free sample for testing and reviewing purposes, but I am so pleased with my experience that I plan to continue using it. I tried the Mint scent and it is strong and invigorating. If you want something more soothing then I would recommend going with the Lavender scent. These are completely my own personal thoughts, opinions, and experiences. I don't know if the company would recommend for use on the face.

column13: Delicious Smelling Serum with positive skin ingredients
column14:
My bf stole my last vitamin C serum which means I have to find a new one. I chose this one for the rosehip oil, vitamin b3 and retinol. I keep this bottle at his house so I can use a vitamin C serum without having him steal mine again.

I have been doing lots of research on vitamin c and the possible effects on long term use. Essentially, it seems to do everything you could wish for and more. This includes the following:

* Repair and renew skin cells
* Stimulate the creation of collagen
* Manages and removes free radicals from skin
* Brighten skin tone

I knew based on the research that I wanted a vitamin c product with a high concentration. The data proved that a concentration of 6% and higher tends to be more effective. Significant Beauty Anti-Aging Clear Skin Serum contains 20% concentration which is quite good.

Vitamin C comes in several different forms and this product uses sodium ascorbyl phosphate which is actually the most stable form. It allows the serum to be used longer without have to store in the dark and be active without lots of steps before application.

This formula has retinol ( vitamin a) is an antioxidant which can help repair skin and increase collagen production. The rosehip oil will sell in all the moisturizing benefits of the serum. Did I mention this smells delicious? The Ylang Ylang and lavender oils smell yummy.

To use, clean face and apply product. This comes with a dropper and I use about a full dropper per use.

Results can take up to a month to really see and appreciate. After initial use, I was pleased with the simplicity of ingredients and results. It will take time to see the long terms goals but with this serum it can be possible. When using any product with vitamin C, please use sunscreen. Vitamin c can cause photo-sensitivity which can lead to sun damage if you don't use sunscreen.

I received this product at low/no cost in exchange for my honest opinion. No monetary compensation was given to me.

column6: Aztec Secret Indian Healing Clay Deep Pore Cleansing
column13: Would recommend for sensitive and oily skin
column14:
I have oily and sensitive skin, and I've struggled with acne for the past few years. I'm very cautious about what to put on my face since many products have only irritated it.

Easy to use, plus this thing lasts forever.

I mix it with either water or apple vinegar and mix/mash it in a ziploc bag for easy disposal and storage for any left over.

Love how this feels. I can feel my face pulsating from the clay shrinking and squeezing my pores. I can so notice a significant difference with consistent use: less breakouts, and any breakouts that do occur are much smaller.

Applying and removing can be a bit of a hassle though. I splash water on my face to soften the clay again before removing with baby wipes.

column6: Clinicians Complex Tissue Growth Factor, 1.0 Ounce
column13: This one delivers and does not disappoint  I tried many before this product that didnt work & much higher priced.
column14:
I had dinner the other night with a Plastic Surgeon & his wife. He asked me what I do at 50+ yrs to have such gorgeous skin. I told him
for starters I didnt cook in the sun my young years. Yes I would go to the beach and get a nice tan, but I always covered my face by wearing
big brim hats and big sunglasses. My Mother and Grandmother taught me to take care of my skin in my teen years so I never allowed my skin
to sunburn. With that said, as you age your face still begins the signs of aging. For me its the smile lines around my nose & mouth. So I study many hours on my own what works in this mirage of products on the market. I realized "Medical Grade" or Pharma Grade is always going to be more potent with the reputable companies like Clinicians. This particular Tissue Growth Factor is being used by some Plastic Surgeons to actually feed the skin cells and regenerate tissue. If you dont you will age and wrinkle. So I spoke with my Dr. friend and he said oh you really have done your homework. He carries this product along with a few others for his clients who have chosen to avoid surgery, or whom have had surgery & want to maintain a youthful appearance. He was very helpful and assured me Im on the right track. I love the feel of this cream. It feels awesome when you apply it. This company did not send me free product. i bought it off of Amazon at a much more reasonable price.
You will hear alot out here in the market about "Tissue Growth Factor". Well this one delivers. For the gals & even guys 30+ I would start now with this type product. If I had had this at 30 I dont believe I would have these laugh lines around my mouth and nose, however this is helping already and I've only used it a few times. Love this one. Good job Clinicians. You have a customer for life.

column6: Cool Mist Humidifier,Oak Leaf 1.3L Multi-Color Room Humidifiers Ultrasonic Essential Oil Diffuser,Large Capacity,7 Color LED Lights,Waterless Auto Shut-Off
column13: Nice Diffuser!! Love the large capacity!!
column14:
I really like this diffuser!!

***PROS***
- It's has a large volume water capacity so you don't have to refill it often.
- Because it holds a lot of water it lasts a lot longer before shutting off.
- Simple design, not big and flashy, it can have the blue light or no blue light.
- High and low mist speeds.

***CONS***
- It doesn't say what type of plastic it is made out of, so I'm not sure if it is BPS, and BPF free (or JUST BPA free) or if I'm putting those chemicals in the air with this diffuser.
- I'm not sure the essential oil is dispersed in continuous amounts throughout the whole cycle it runs - meaning, it seems to be more potent in the first hour or two but I'm not sure it's giving out the same amount of scent after about 2 or 3 hours - it seems more potent at the beginning.
- Directions didn't translate to English very well.
- Directions said the on/off buttons for the light and the mist were on the opposite sides than what they were.
- It beeps twice when it runs out, loud enough to hear it but not super loud, but it could wake you up if you had this running while you were sleeping. Also I wish there was a way to turn off the beep when you turn it on, it beeps once for high, click again - beep again for low and click again and beeps twice to turn off. And the light beeps once when you turn it on and off. I wish there was a way to make it not beep because beeping has a tendency to startle our dogs because it sounds like a fire alarm beep to them.

Overall for the price I would say this is a good diffuser, I would recommend it, but I can't give it 5-stars for the reasons listed above.

column6: ZAQ Noor Multi Color Litemist Aromatherapy Essential Oil Diffuser
column14:
[[VIDEOID:5555940dab86cd10f151f56ac00b04a3]] I'm an essential oil enthusiast and own multiple diffusers. The Zaq Noor Multicolor Diffuser holds 80ml of water and is on the smaller side of my diffuser collection, but puts off more mist than some of my much larger models. Since it doesn't use heat, my oils keep their benefits and integrity.

The diffuser cycles through bright LED light in a range of beautiful, vibrant colors. I can push the single button to turn it on and begin this cycle. A second time to hold on the color of my preference, a 3rd time to dim the lights and a 4th time to turn the unit off. It operates quietly and cannot be heard unless I'm within 2 feet of the diffuser. When I can hear it, the water bubbling inside sounds like a babbling brook and I like it enough to keep it next to my head in bed at night.

Even though the diffuser holds only 80ml of water, in can operate continuously for 4 hours. It will shut off automatically if the water level becomes too low, so I can turn it on before bed and not have to worry.

All things considered, I'm very pleased with the overall quality and function of the Zaq Noor Litemist Diffuser. I'm happy with the amount of mist, ease of use and the included measuring cup is convenient for knowing exactly how much water to put in.

column6: Waterpik Aquarius Water Flosser
column13: YUCK.  DO NOT BUY THIS PRODUCT
column14:
I rate this product as ZERO stars. Not just bad, not just defective, not just non-functional, but also disgusting.
When I opened the box, the product had obviously been used and returned, then repackaged and resold.
The plastic bag that holds the tips was ripped open, some of the tips were missing, the remainder had clearly been used, or soiled in some way.
Now, let's think about that, a PRODUCT YOU PUT IN YOUR MOUTH, used, returned, repackaged and resold, dirty.
There are actually laws against that in most states for other products that come into contact with bodily fluids, such as underwear.
If this was done by Amazon fulfillment, they should check their records to see who handled the previous return of this item, and fire someone.
On top of all that, the pump system did not work. I have a PhD in engineering and have designed many health and medical products, so I should be able to figure out how to turn on a waterpik. This one simply does not work. I checked everything including the voltage on the AC line.
SUMMARY:
The product sold to me was previously used but sold AS NEW, it was defective, it was unsanitary, just plain disgusting.
So, in my assessment, the product was defective, then it was probably returned for that reason, repackaged by some thoughtless idiot, and resold as new.
I will not return the product, I'll keep it for show and tell. In my profession and for my many students, it will be an excellent example of everything that could possibly go wrong with the marketing and sale of a health/medical product. For that purpose it is worth the $60.

NOTE: in 15 years of on-line shopping, this is only the second negative review I have ever written. I hope it has a positive effect.

column6: Lab Series SPF 35 BB Tinted Moisturizer Broad Spectrum for Men, 1.7 Ounce
column13: For Those New to Tinted Moisturizers...
column14:
First off, IT IS pretty much makeup, but it is very subtle. Only you will see a difference, but you will definitely see a difference. In the three months or so I have been wearing this I have never been asked if I was wearing makeup. And in the conservative rural area I live in, folks would call me out and label me a tranny if they could tell.

Moving on, it should work with about any Caucasian skin tone. Before it's rubbed in it may look darker or lighter than your skin (it's darker in my case), but it evens out incredibly well.

So what does it do? It makes your skin look healthier, evened out, and minimizes the appearance of pores. Definitely doesn't give a flat fake powdery look though - even up close.

SPF is legit. I was out in the sun all day on a Saturday recently and fried my shoulders/chest/back to the point the skin eventually peeled - there wasn't even redness on the bridge of my nose with this applied earlier that day.

I have oily sensitive skin prone to breakouts if I am not careful. This does not irritate my skin or cause breakouts, thankfully. In all honesty, I think I have had less acne since I've started using this, but it could be due to not using a daily moisturizer before using this. And on that note, I do use this 6 to 7 days a week. No problems.

One tube should last you two months roughly - even if you use it most days like me. It has been about three months for me and it's just now getting low (just bought a second tube for when I am actually out, to be honest). That said, at $35 a tube it's not cheap by any means and that's its biggest downfall for me.

Another con is it will rub off of your face if you wipe your face with a shirt, towel, napkin, pillows or whatever similar. But at the same time you don't have to be super cautious of touching your face to anything. You can still put white shirts on over your head and scratch the occasional face itch with it on.

Final thoughts - It does what it says it will do, and it does that excellently. It's great for people like me with uneven skin tones due to dark spots from acne (or similar) who want to even their skin out without looking at-all fake. But for those with great even skin already, I can't see much justification for the price - But I won't say it won't do anything good for you either.

column6: Neutrogena Age Shield Face Oil-Free Lotion Sunscreen Broad Spectrum
column13: Useful for Acne Prone Skin ONLY on Occasional Basis
column14: I give this product 3 stars because it does what it says it supposed to do, which is provide excellent sun protection, however it didn‚Äôt meet my expectation for what I specifically needed it for. I currently and have had a history of acne prone skin that has left unfortunate marks of hyperpigmentation on my skin from bad flare ups in response hormonal acne. I was looking for a daily sunscreen with a very high SPF, to help fade the hyperpigmentation, and further protect my skin on a daily basis to prevent aging. I also was interested in having  high SPF because I live in a beach town and therefore go to the beach frequently in the summer time. While this product did amply protect my skin from the sun, it appeared to make my skin congested, and did cause breakouts. I know that the product protected my skin very well because when I would go to the beach I would apply this product to my face and like Coppertone SPF 70 to the rest of my body to protect my skin and pace the progression of my tan through out the summer. While I would get a nice tan on my body my face was indeed notably lighter (like 2 shades lighter) than my body, after a day at the beach. This was refreshing because it kind of saves us ladies from the whole runaround of chasing darker foundations through out the summer that are no longer usable during the winter because it leaves that unsightly distinction between your face and your neck that eventually goes back to its normal color. I appreciated this aspect of the product because typically women who have acne prone skin have to purchase quality foundations/products that are high end and expensive to avoid breakouts. I‚Äôm a mixed race black whose skin tone falls anywhere between 3-4 maybe half way into 5 according to theFitzpatrick Skin Tone chart depending on how much I beach it up in the summer time on the . I do have brown eyes and hair. Which also brings me to mention that if you are of color or have olive or darker skin(3 skin tone or higher) ifyou wear the lotion with out makeup it will  be apparent on your skin, and give of an ashy like, or what people describe a purplish look on your skin when, and especially if you are perspire on the beach.  So with all that said I reserve this product for when I‚Äôm out in the sun for extended periods of time like 4-6 hours or more, and or when I go travel on vacation to warmer climates (southern U.S./tropics). It‚Äôs not a daily SPF for those with acne prone skin. Again I would like to share that the product did not wreak havoc on my skin. Using it on occasion did not cause like damaging self-esteem acne, I could just tell the product congested my skin (a pimple or two here and there after application). This didn‚Äôt worry me too much. For instances as I described above such as vacations etc., I will keep this product and just make sure that I certainly use the deep cleansing brush in conjunction with my Clarisonic to ensure that I get as much product out of my pores after use.  In conclusion, this product will remain in my cosmetic skin care arsenal, but I will continue to use Clinique‚Äôs City sunblock SPF 40 for my daily sunscreen until I find a higher SPF that wont break me out.

column6: BH Cosmetics 120 Color Eyeshadow Palette 2nd Edition
column14:
This is a great palette for a beginner who wants to experiment with lots of things. I do a lot of stage looks and dramatic huge eye looks. I was tired to buying new colors every time and having tons of loose pans floating around. This is perfect for experimenting with color without spending tons of money on individual shadows. When I find color combinations I love, I might buy higher end makeup to use in the future.

This makeup is really chalky and you can expect fallout with just about every color if you're not meticulous. Definitely use an eye primer or it won't really stay on at all. I use Urban Decay's eye primer potion and it's very effective with this palette. The colors in the pans look a lot darker than when they're applied, so swatch things to get a better idea of color matching. Everything is very pigmented, but chalky.

I have EXTREMELY sensitive skin, so pretty much everything irritates it. So don't read too deeply into that part of the review. Finding things I can use without irritation is impossible.

column6: Panasonic Milano All-in-One Trimmer, ER-GB40-S, for Beard and Mustache, with 19 Trim Adjustable Settings, Cordless, Wet/Dry
column13: One of the best, most precise trimmers I have owned
column14:
One of the best, most precise trimmers I have owned. it replaces a 14 year old Remington that the battery pack died on.

I've purchased several trimmers by different makers before this, to a one, the motors in them were all rather weak seeming. While the Panasonic is quiet, it seems "strong" enough and gets the job done.

Putting a blade on my neck at any time except the winter causes a lot of skin irritation no matter what method or products used. So, most of the year, I "shave" from my jawline down with a trimmer. This one cuts the hair shorter than any one I've owned. The instructions say it will cut, without the comb in place, to 1/64th of an inch. On me, it will shorten it so that appears like a mild "5 O'clock shadow". The Comb is twist adjustable in mm measurements, which is handy indeed.

It is a wet/dry trimmer, but I don't trim my beard in the shower. I don't know anyone who does. It is, however, handy to be able to use running water to clean the trimmer. the cutter head pops off and re-inserts easily, with no small parts to break or weaken.

All in all, an excellent product.

column14:
I received this product for free in exchange for this honest and unbiased review. I got this for my mother and she thoroughly enjoys it. The packaging was good with the item being encased in cardboard with La Creme branding.

According the my mother, the face cream does prevent fine lines and wrinkles over a period of a few days. The cream also goes on smooth and doesn‚Äôt leave any visible signs of its application. It also does not cause any burning or irritation.

Overall this is a great skin cream for reducing wrinkles and making you look younger. Other reviews on Amazon do not focus on the product, rather they focus on the company making the product. The product itself is high quality and works as advertised, I would not have a problem recommending this to anyone.

JUST got here and I adore it.

column13: One of Nars most awesome products & the only Illuminator I will use having mature 50+ skin.  You will love it I promise
column14:
Absolutely awesome Illuminator in this Copacabana shade. The best way to apply this creamy Illuminator is to use the Nars Pore Perfecter for Oily skin under it first. I have mature, dry skin so using the Perfecter for oily skin is to make the Illuminator & then make up set properly and look good. The Nars Pore Perfecter for Dry skin will not set my makeup in this horrid humid, hot tropical climate, so make sure to get the one for oily skin as it sets your makeup whether going out for the day or evening. Make sure you wait and let the pore perfecter dry into your skin, then apply
the illuminator & let it set, then apply your make up. I use from light to heavy liquid foundations, but my daughter uses mineral powder make up
and it does just as well. The entire trick to success in setting your make up to stay put is the Pore Perfecter for oily skin. The one for dry skin
would not set my make up all day or all night and got drippy after a couple of hrs. So save your $$ & go right to the one for oily skin.

column14:

Remember you can always add a bit more if needed but if you overdo, you will look like you need to wash your hair.

column6: Emjoi AP-18 Emagine Dual Opposed 72 Tweezer Head Epilator
column13: Less pain than the Braun Silk Epil 5!
column14: I purchased this after using the Braun Silk-Epil5 for about a year. The Braun epilator was my very first experience with epilation and it definitely took some getting used to dealing with the pain. But once I saw the hairless results, I was hooked on epilation! Being of Indian decent, I'm a female who unfortunately has battled with every form of hair removal with little success - until I found epilation. After about a year of using the Braun with little decrease or resistance build up to the pain I started searching for another alternative and found the Emoji Ap-18. After reading such positive reviews I decided to bite the bullet and make the purchase and haven't looked back since! The Emoji is so much less painful that the Braun! I guess the 72 heads help minimize the pain, although on the flip side, I find that the Emoji doesn't get as many as the finer, smaller hairs that the Braun used to. Although I have to make a few more passes with the Emoji than I had to with the Braun, it's totally worth it due to the minimized pain levels! I definitely recommend the Emoji AP-18 to anyone looking for an efficient, low pain (no epilator will be pain free) Epilator.

column13: Sea Salt for Bath or Body Scrub is a Win-Win
column14:
After a week or so of not sleeping well, I was delighted to indulge in a relaxing bath filled with the Adovia Genuine Dead Sea Salts. A warm bath often helps relax me before bed, but it helps when I have an additive like the Adovia Genuine Dead Sea Salts in my bath water. The water in my neighborhood is from a rural well and many people in the area have a water softener. I don't have one, so I appreciate what these salts can do for my skin and the overall body effects.

column14:
I love this thing.
My facial growth is almost but not quite that I can shave every other day. Usually shave every day, but if I skip a day, other shavers tended to miss hairs and patches left and right, and I'd have to use the trimmer a lot. Wasn't so much the shavers, more what I was doing.

The interceptor middle blades are SO so much better than having to use the trimmer to get all the missed hairs when growth is longer. Or when changing / removing a mustache or beard or sideburns or whatever. I'd looked for ages for something like this. However it may not be for everyone.

It's hard to say, as a recommendation, depends too much on what works for you, for any individual. This setup just happened to work great for what I needed. No great insight, different people feel comfortable with different types and models. Just really happy at finally finding a type that works well for me after years of searching and trying different shavers.
