column6: Shea Butter
column13: excellent for very dry skin and skin recovery, good for climber too
column14: I have very dry skin which is so dry that I need moisturizer all year round even in humid climate. In winter it cracks and is flaky. Last winter I bought this unrefined ivory shea butter, it's the best moisturizer I've ever tried. It soothed my painful cracking skin immediately and my overall skin condition improved in the winter. I'm also a climber that means I always torture my finger skin until my fingertips so sore and sometimes even bruise and can't climb anymore. I've tried some hand cream specifically designed for climbers for skin recovery, it worked. As a active climber, I need skin recovery quick so I tested to put climber hand cream on one hand and shea butter on the other hand. The next morning I compare them, the finger skin on the hand which I put shea butter is obviously better. Now I put shea butter on my hands after every climbing day before going to bed and other nights too if I remember. ps: I have used this shea butter plain or mixed with olive oil. Both worked equally well. But the latter is creamier and easier to apply especially in winter when plain shea butter became so solid and took more time to melt in my hands before I could apply them on my body.

column6: De La Cruz Sulfur Ointment Acne Medication 2.6oz
column14:
UPDATE:: When I first used this product I did like some other reviews did and left it on overnight to speed up the process. That worked, and it really dried out my pimples, BUT, if you don't stay on top of your moisturizing game, you will definitely suffer the consequences...I had a really bad breakout on the upper bridge of my nose and slathered this stuff on overnight for like 2 or 3 nights in a row, and lordy...the dried skin made it look worse once this stuff kicked in. I learned my lesson for sure. So now when I use it, I use it at night, but I wipe it off with a cloth after like 2 or 3 hours. I find this works best on the more cystic type of acne, but if you put a tiny bit on a whitehead and wipe it off after a few hours, it shrinks them up a little and dries them out. Derm prescribed me azelaic cream because I needed something safe I could take while trying to get pregnant, but it made things much worse! So I stopped using it. Overall, Ill continue with this product, as it's the only thing that's really working for me at the moment...

ORIGINAL REVIEW:
I just received my sulfur ointment. I excitedly washed my face and dabbed this on all my active pimples. Ever since I got off birth control my hormonal acne has just gotten worse and worse by the day. I thought I was past acne, as I'm 34! Not so I guess...once an acne sufferer, always an acne sufferer I guess. As a teenager into my 20s I suffered from cystic acne and regular whitehead pimples. Usually around my jawline and upper neck/ right under my chin area, also around my hairline by my ears and sometimes cheeks. The only place clear at the moment is my forehead and cheeks! :(
I'm leaving this spot treatment on until we go out later on tonight. So probably like 4 hours. I will definitely update my review once I've given this product time to work.

column6: Jaowying Beauty Body Scrub Blueberry - Best Scrub NET 5.07 Ounces / 150 G.
column14:
One of the most important step of skin care is exfoliation. Disgustingly enough, our skin cells die quite often, and exfoliating is what keeps your skin looking gorgeous despite that. In order to keep your skin looking bright, fresh and youthful, you ave to slough away the gunky build-up that makes it entirely dull and boring. So what makes a good body exfoliant? It truly depends on your skin type and the results you are looking for, but for the most part, an exfoliant should contain some kind of abrasive ingredient to do the exfoliating, and then other ingredients that collaborate to deliver your desired results. I recently tried Jaowying Blueberry Body Scrub, and it's really a great gentle Summertime body scrub.

When it comes to exfoliation, for my skin, the more abrasive, the better. I mean, I don't want to wash up with shards of glass, but I need it to plow through the dead skin cells to reveal what's hiding underneath. I feel like I have really fast cell turnover or something. Like, I could totally exfoliate every single day and it would not irritate my skin whatsoever. That being said, it's typically recommended to do it twice a week. I have been using this a couple of times per week to keep my skin looking Summer fresh and it seriously does make a difference in the texture of my skin immediately after using it. It reminds me a bit of an in-shower lotion almost, because it leaves this silky layer of smooth behind. It smells really good too! As far as being a scrub, this is a gentle scrub for sure. It won't leave your skin irritated or sensitive, but will leave your skin feeling softer than before. The jar of Blueberry Body Scrub is 5 fl oz so it will not last forever. I found that I had to use quite a bit per use, and I even kept it to just my legs. I could foresee this lasting about a month or a month and a half depending on how sparingly you use it. I also think it would be convenient in a squeeze bottle. Normally I don't think of a scrub that way, but as I said, this one is very much like an in-shower body lotion, and I feel it would serve well in a tube versus a jar. I received this item complimentary in exchange for an honest review. The opinions and experiences detailed above are entirely my own.

column6: Basic Acne Treatment Kit by Exposed Skin Care: For all skin types, 60 day supply (Cleanser, Toner, Dual Treatment Serums)
column14: I'm 20 and have horrible, all over my face acne since I was 12. For six years, I used proactiv. While it definitely helped, my skin was never really totally "clear" and always had this horrible, bleached, greyish hue to it. When I decided to quit proactiv five months ago, my skin freaked out. It had never looked worse and there were days where I didn't even want to leave my house because I was so embarrassed of the way my skin looked. I tried everything shy of returning to proactiv, but absolutely nothing even helped. When I found exposed, I was obviously skeptical because of the overwhelming number of positive reviews but I was so desperate for a solution that I was willing to try anything. Two months later, my skin is completely clear. Every time I look in the mirror I want to cry because I'd never thought my skin would look this good. Not only is it clear, but the old scars I had have started to fade, my pores look smaller, and the skin on my face is no longer bleached and dead-looking. I will say that in the first two weeks, my skin got much worse before it got better. I know that acne can be frustrating, and that everybody wants a miracle product that will clear their skin immediately, but you really do have to give the system time to work.

column6: Nice Dreams Sleep Mask with Earplugs Satin Carry Bag and Wide Strap - Excellent Quality - Satisfaction Guaranteed
column13: Surprisingly strong fumes make this unwearable
column14: Even though most of the reviews are fake, I decided to take a chance on these. A couple reviews seemed real and I must have received a different product from those reviewers. I bought this mask during a lightning sale a few days ago so I paid just under ten dollars. Even at the sale price, this is overpriced. Based on the quality I wouldn't pay more than five or six dollars for this mask. I buy my earplugs in bulk because I throw them out every other day for sanitation, so the single pair of earplugs isn't worth another four or five dollars to me. Plus they're quite large compared to the earplugs I buy and would probably give me an ear ache. I buy [[ASIN:B0051U7W32 Mack's Ear Care Ultra Soft Foam Earplugs, 50 Pair]] and the plugs that come with mask seem to be about 1 1/2 times the diameter. Also, for same sale price, you can get a mask here on Amazon that's shaped around the eye so there's nothing touching your eyelids while you sleep, which I think I would prefer.  Still I would have kept the mask because I don't usually return stuff that's functional even if I overpaid. But this mask smells awful. For something so small, the fumes coming off it are intense. I didn't notice it when I opened the package and I even tried it on for a couple seconds to test the light blocking and didn't notice an odor. Then it sat airing out on my night table for at least 10 hours before I went to sleep. Before going to sleep, while I was lying in bed, it sat a foot away from my head and I still couldn't smell it. But when I put it on... hoo boy. Because it sits less than a inch from my nostrils, it's impossible to avoid. Within a minute, I was starting to get a headache and my eyes were burning. It feels silly to return something that cost less than ten dollars but this mask is unwearable to someone like me who is odor-sensitive.  EDIT:  Before packaging the set up for return, I compared the size of the earplugs. They are the same diameter as Mack's but they are a much stiffer foam.

column6: Aquis Exfoliating Back Scrubber
column13: Works Great On Back AND Other Hard To Reach Areaa
column14:
This product was purchased because due to failed back surgeries, I have a hard time reaching certain areas of my body. The rougher side of the Scrubber is great on the back, and even works on the calluses of the feet when I use it while sitting on a chair in the shower.

The smoother side accomplishes what I REALLY bought this item for: cleaning the area the toilet paper doesn't quite get clean enough. Soaping up the smooth side and using a back and forth motion while placing the Scrubber between my legs cleans that area PERFECTLY. Then rinsing the Scrubber thoroughly, then soaping and rinsing again gets it nice and clean for the next use.

I tried several so-called "Butt scrubbers" and "Hiney Cleaners", all of which had plastic handles supporting some sort of cleaning material. These items were cheaply made, and every one I bought was broken after one or two uses. The Aquis Exfoliating Back Scrubber accomplishes the task perfectly, and more than likely will not break or tear apart for quite some time if I take good care of it.

I bought another one as a gift for my brother and his wife.

column6: Primal Pit Paste Natural Deodorant, Aluminum Free, Paraben Free, No Added Fragrances
column13: This stuff actually works....even if you're a super sweaty gal like me!
column14:
I loveeeeee this stuff. Now let me tell you, I'm not one of those girls that only sweats a little and can get away with wearing most natural deodorants. I sweat. A lot.

I've been trying to find a natural deodorant that you know, actually works. One that doesn't make me start smelling my own BO around 10am. Tried a lot of them, all same result. Works fine for a solid 1-2 hours, then the stink sinks through. And don't even think about putting it on before the gym unless you want to be THAT person who doesn't wear deodorant.

But, alas! An all natural deodorant that actually works!! My boyfriend first bought the unscented one which I naturally thought would be bad news for me by the end of the day being around his sweaty self. But no....he didn't smell at all! So I did the thing girlfriends do and I stole some of his deodorant and was really surprised...and then stole it again the next day....and the next day until I was caught! So I bought some of my own and because I'm a girl and like to smell pretty I went with the lavender. I'm pretty sensitive to smells and the amount of smellyness from this is perfect - it's just enough to make you feel fabulous but not enough to make your eyes water.

I think this stuff actually works better than a lot of regular deodorants out there in general. Three cheers for Primal Paste!

It is very delicate so I worry about long lasting durability. I've only worn it twice so far, so it's too soon to tell. I have toddler boys - so it's durability will be tested for sure. I like that it is adjustable. It's easy to pull it to the length you prefer, and stays in place so far. My only complaints are 1: the ring that the clasp attaches to is so tiny. column13: Around 10 years ago I purchased a cloth that was the best silver polisher I had ever had
column14: All my jewelry is silver.  Around 10 years ago I purchased a cloth that was the best silver polisher I had ever had.  It was a two layered one, just like this.  Well that cloth lasted for many years but eventually it was done.  Other cloths were bought, I used a very expensive cream I saw a demo of, a liquid cleaner also.  NOTHING WAS shining and keeping the silver I wore from tarnishing UNTIL I saw this on Amazon and read the reviews, Can this be the the same or just like that double cloth I bought 10 years ago.  It arrived last week and I took off all my dirty looking bracelets. First I used the white cloth, it removed tarnish that had been there for 3 years or so...next I used to blue cloth to buff it up and it sparkled.  Still does.  Never any of those bogus silver cleaners for me again!!!!! This is the only one.

column6: King Will BASIC 8mm White Tungsten Ring Wedding Band Step Edge Brushed Center Any Size
column13: Will you marry me?  Pretty please?
column14:
I know that's sort of sudden given that we just met, but...well...this ring is awesome, and sometimes I feel silly wearing it around without actually being married.

But I still do. Seriously, this is one fantastic looking and comfortable ring. Looking at the pictures here, and then after unboxing it (and these do come in a nice presentation box), I wasn't sure if I'd really like the matte finish on the center region. It seemed kind of boring. Yeah, I was totally wrong. Completely, utterly wrong. I love it.

I feel like I'd just babble about this ring, so I'll try to simply convey that it is very comfortable and looks (IMO) even better in person once you have it on. King Will makes several similar styles, and I've tried three of them: this one, [[ASIN:B00X3J36Z6 one with a beveled edge]], and [[ASIN:B010N89158 one with a different style of beveled edge]]. I honestly like all three of them.

As you likely already well know, tungsten carbide is not the same as pure tungsten. However, it is also much less expensive and has a lot of similar qualities - which is one reason why it is so popular for rings these days. What makes these rings so strong can also make them brittle, so rather than deforming like a gold band would if you hit it hard enough, these can crack. That's just a note, as you definitely don't have to baby these things.

Pros:
(*) Looks exactly like the product image, so if you like the pictures you should like the look of the ring in person (or, if you're like me, you'll like it more in person)
(*) Comfortable with smooth surfaces everywhere

Cons:
(*) Might cause your eyes to burn when you, albeit innocently, startle someone by spontaneously proposing in the line at Chipotle...and they break out the pepper spray. The silver lining, though, is that there will be tortillas all around to mop up and enjoy that spicy goodness

(I received a free sample for an evaluation and honest review.)for an evaluation and honest review.)

column6: Geff House Jewelry Organizer Box with Lock & Travel Case
column14: The quality and workmanship of the Geff House Jewelry organizer box is wonderful.  The Jewelry box not only keeps all the jewelry organized and neatly tucked away, it comes with a lock closure with a key.  The jewelry organizer box is a black PU padded leather on the outside.  The inside is a grey velvet like material that keeps your jewelry from tarnishing.  The jewelry organizer actually holds a ton of jewelry.  There are two pull out drawers and top jewelry tray in the organizer.  There are two fold out necklace/bracelet compartments on each side of the organizer that snap closed.  Each fold out side hold 4 necklaces or bracelets, and had an elastic looking bag near the bottom to keep the chains from hanging out of the organizer.  The top jewelry tray has many compartments, one that has a row of ring holders, there are 6 earring cards, that act as dividers, they are removable so if you don't need that many or want them at all, you can just use that compartment for a different piece of jewelry.  The compartments in the top tray are of various sizes that can hold watches, bracelets, necklaces, or earrings.  The jewelry organizer top opens up when you press the sides of the front lock closure, if its not locked.  When opened, the inside of the top has small mirror inside to help you see when you're putting on your jewelry.  It also has a long elastic pocket to hold other jewelry pieces as well.  When closed, the top has a handle that makes carrying and taking it on the go quite easy.  There are two pull out drawers in the jewelry organizer.  One is a thinner drawer with two different sections of the same size.  The other drawer is about double in length and has 4 different sections, two smaller sections in the left back, one medium sized section in the left front part of the drawer.  The fourth section is the entire right side with no divided sections.  Inside of that section is also a travel jewelry box.  In that travel jewelry box holds the key to the organizer lock.  The travel jewelry box, which is a black PU leather from the outside and the grey velvet on the inside just like the larger jewelry organizer.  When you open the travel jewelry box, is it divided in a section with a ring holder, a flat section for necklaces or bracelets, and the third with earring cards that act as dividers as well.  This jewelry box is much more than I expected.  Its great quality, visually appealing, has the lock closure.  It holds quite a bit of jewelry and my collection isn't small at all.  I love that It has a carrying handle on the top as well so I can take it with me quickly if I need to. I also love that it has a travel jewelry box.  I don't have to stuff my jewelry into ziploc style bags now.  I love this jewelry box and the quality of it, this would also make a great gift for a jewelry lover.  Promotional discount provided in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

column13: These earrings are great. I have multiple ear piercings and am always ...
column14: These earrings are great. I have multiple ear piercings and am always buying studs that vary in size, so that i can have them go from big to small or vice versa. I also like these because I feel like the smaller sizes are good to wear second and third  ear piercings without seeming to big or awkward. I also really like how these earrings are packaged as the three smaller sizes come together on one card while the three larger ones come on a separate card.   If you only have one or two piercings I think the bigger sizes would be great for everyday use and if you are like me with multiple ear piercings I feel you will get a lot of use out of this set being able to mix and match the various earrings sizes. Overall I feel that these are perfect for everyday wear.  I did receive this product at a discount for an honest and unbiased review.

Silver should not come into contact with harsh household chemicals such as bleach, ammonia, or chlorine.

column13: Discolored spots & slightly different products sold under same name.
column14:
I bought my first of ring in June. I'm getting married in September so I haven't even worn it yet, other than trying it on to make sure it fits. It's sat in the black "sack" that it was shipped to me in. I pulled it out to show a friend recently and noticed that it has some discolourations on it. They're slightly darkened areas that almost resemble burn marks. Not extremely noticeable, but still a disappointment because now I'm past my return policy and am stuck with it. Luckily it was cheap and I still have time to find a more suitable ring before the wedding. I suppose I can keep this ring to wear when I'm in situations that I don't want to get my next ring lost or harmed.

The issues continue... I decided to try this one more time because I really don't dislike this ring, if only it weren't discolored. I tried ordering 1 more only to later realize that they didn't come to me from Metals Jewelry, but from "Gnex" in China. This 2nd ring was lighter in weight and just felt cheaper all-around. The first ring had a classy "White Tungsten Carbide" stamp on the inside... the 2nd ring had a blurry/sloppy "White Tungsten Ring" stamped on the inside. Thanks for the permanent reminder that this is a ring, I guess?

I guess I should have paid more attention when I purchased, but it seems strange to me that the products shipped from Metals Jewelry and Gnex are so different, but being sold under the same name. Also, when I ordered from Metals Jewelry I got Prime shipping and free returns; ordering from Gnex meant I had to pay for return shipping and only get a "partial" refund. Be careful of that.

So far it seems like the comparably priced "Oxford Ivy" Tungsten rings are a way better bang for the buck and way more consistent in quality. I'd recommend those instead of this ring. They're more silver/grey in color, but better value.

column6: King Will BASIC Unisex 8MM Tungsten Carbide Ring Wedding Band Matte Finished Center Comfort Fit
column13: Hi, I'm Adam.  Will you marry me?
column14:
I know that's sort of sudden given that we just met, but...well...this ring is awesome, and sometimes I feel silly wearing it around without actually being married.

But I still do. Seriously, this is one fantastic looking and comfortable ring. Looking at the pictures here, and then after unboxing it (and these do come in a nice presentation box), I wasn't sure if I'd really like the matte finish on the center region. It seemed kind of boring. Yeah, I was totally wrong. Completely, utterly wrong. I love it.

I feel like I'd just babble about this ring, so I'll try to simply convey that it is very comfortable and looks (IMO) even better in person once you have it on. King Will makes several similar styles, and I've tried three of them: this one, [[ASIN:B00X3J36Z6 one with a different polished edge around the matte finish]], and [[ASIN:B010N8ATBS one with a stepped edge]]. I honestly like all three of them.

As you likely already well know, tungsten carbide is not the same as pure tungsten. However, it is also much less expensive and has a lot of similar qualities - which is one reason why it is so popular for rings these days. What makes these rings so strong can also make them brittle, so rather than deforming like a gold band would if you hit it hard enough, these can crack. That's just a note, as you definitely don't have to baby these things.

Pros:
(*) Looks exactly like the product image, so if you like the pictures you should like the look of the ring in person (or, if you're like me, you'll like it more in person)
(*) Comfortable with smooth surfaces everywhere

Cons:
(*) Might cause your eyes to burn when you, albeit innocently, startle someone by spontaneously proposing in the line at Chipotle...and they break out the pepper spray. The silver lining, though, is that there will be tortillas all around to mop up and enjoy that spicy goodness

(I received a free sample for an evaluation and honest review.)uation and honest review.)

This is a sleek and durable bracelet. At first glance I thought it was leather, but its silicone. I love the combination of stainless steel mixed with silicone. Its comfortable enough to wear all day and you can't tell its on for the most part. My husband says if you are working on repairs you might want to take it off as the steel rubs up against other items. Easy to open on your own and close without requiring someone else to do it for you. This can dress up a plain outfit quite a bit. One small issue is the clasp. I am not sure if it will hold up but will update in a few months. My husband wears this bracelet a few times a week right now. I do love the pouch it comes with to help keep it protected from other elements.

I received this product at a deep discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased opinion.

column6: Earring & Necklace Organizer - Acrylic Folding Jewelry Holder Screen - Holds 128 Pairs of Earrrings
column14:
Pros:
- Perfect for large Earring Collections
- Good selling display for earrings
- Has a lot of space when closed

Cons:
- Some necklaces and bracelets are not as practical

I got this with the idea that I may display some sets of my jewelry on here. Overall I don't think I will be doing that as I don't like the look of it but I do think if my stud collection gets large enough this will be the perfect display for collectors and sellers. If you are displaying something in a space where you can walk around this is also a nice idea. You can put some on the front and some on the back that way when you close it the pieces wont touch and will fit more. I tried putting some bracelets on it and I didn't like it as much but double wrapping necklaces seemed fine. It's great for travel sellers or to take with you on a trip.
Mine does creak a lot when I open and close it.

I received this product at a complimentary discount for my honest and unbiased review.

column6: Moon Wings Vintage Men's Ring Stainless Steel Ring
column13: ... Moon Wings and found their rings to be of nice quality and luster
column14:
I previously ordered from Moon Wings and found their rings to be of nice quality and luster. This ring has some weight to it but I enjoy the feeling of it on my hand, it's by no means heavy but it's a nice solid ring. Really nice luster on it, these rings seems to hold up well as well. I've had my other rings for 2 or 3 months by Moon Rings and there isn't a scratch on it. I expect no less than this vintage model ring. The design is nice on the rings face and has good detail. Sometimes it pays to spend a couple extra bucks to get a better quality item that will hold up, sometimes it doesn't but this is one of those times that I am 100% satisfied.

I rated it 4 stars because unlike my first order, the size was off, I could swear this ring is a 10.5 instead of the 10 I ordered. So order this ring a half size or size smaller than normally. Great product otherwise, no other complaints.

Will buy from this seller again. 2015-08-14 US 12027989 R17MSV8IWTNP4Z B00UV7460C 909514886 Rhodium-Plated Sterling Silver Hoop Earrings Jewelry 2 1 3 N Y Two Stars Smaller than I thought it would be and not impressed with quality 2015-08-14 US 47832884 R2IE1V1KPPO9EM B00CQ11KNC 435025842 TOMTOP 20pcs Colorful Stainless Steel Rhinestone Curved Nose Studs Rings Bars Piercing (Multicolor1) Jewelry 3 0 0 N Y Bargain price, but crooked stones and allergic reaction to the glue You certainly get what you pay for with these. I can't complain about the price, they are very affordable, and they were shipped quickly. I got one of each color, with some that had slight variations, such as three different shades of pink. Overall, I got a light and a dark of each color with a crystal, an AB, and a hematite. The bar is a bit long but i have a nose that can accommodate that. I wouldn't recommend these for folks with thin nostrils or a septum that extends below the outer edge of the nostril. The bar and curve will be regularly visible, and metallic boogies aren't really cute.

My main issue is with the stones. They are glued on, but some are glued on at very wonky angles, looking like they will fall off at any minute, sideways, crooked, off-center. I am also super bummed because my favorite color stone has a large dab of glue on the outside of the metal cup, the part that rests against my nose. I had a HUGE allergic reaction to the glue, and I tried on 3 separate occasions to make sure it was the glue I was reacting to. The skin around the piercing became red and inflamed, painful to the touch, all that other good stuff that looks like an infection. That didn't happen with any of the other pieces which didn't have glue on the outside. If you don't have sensitive skin, or you get pieces without glue spills, you should be fine. I haven't had any reactions to the metal itself, which was my main concern.

All in all, it's a good bargain and the stones are pretty, but there are a couple things to watch out for. Sarah & Andrew

column14:
Losing a pet is so hard. But having a little something that you can wear to remind you of your close bond is a great thing. Not everyone gets their pet cremated so this doesn't have to hold just ashes. It can have a few strands of hair as well. The top unscrews and there is a very small opening to put whatever memento you want inside. It is difficult to get anything in the tiny hole but if you have a small funnel (very small) or you want to use a thin piece of paper to curl it into a funnel, that helps. It just takes a little finagling to get it in and it must be fairly fine ash.

Once in, the top screws back on and has a rubber seal to keep it tightly shut. It might take a bit to arrive so keep that in mind if you are giving it as a gift. It comes with a long chain as well. Shiny and nicely finished. Sample provided for review.

This ring is seriously cool looking, but it does inspire me to think that I'm some sort of dark wizard. It seems to have inspired my neighbor to think that I'm losing it, though. I try to command him to clean my yard, raising my ringed hand with fingers splayed, muttering in...well, English, because it's the only language that I know. So, he can understand me. He just says, \\\"no.\\\\\" I say that he should enjoy his weekends while he still can - because soon I shall master the power of this ring, and my yard will be spotless.

Okay, I'm not actually crazy. Well, maybe, but not because of this ring. In all seriousness, it is very nice. It looks much shinier in person than it does in the product images. In the images, it looks a little dull, but it has a very nice polished surface all around. It's stunning to look at. Black is becoming more popular in rings these days, and there are a number of guys at work that have black wedding bands. Well, or there are more sorcerers than I'd like to think. Anyway, while gold is still the standard, you certainly wouldn't be out of place to choose this. Plus, it's virtually impossible to get a better price. $10-$15 for a ring of this quality? King Will does a very nice job with their rings (I've tried a few) and have always impressed me. Their build quality is rock solid, and the sizing has been consistent.

As you likely already well know, tungsten carbide is not the same as pure tungsten. However, it is also much less expensive and has a lot of similar qualities - which is one reason why it is so popular for rings these days. What makes these rings so strong can also make them brittle, so rather than deforming like a gold band would if you hit it hard enough, these can crack. That's just a note, as you definitely don't have to baby these things.

Pros:
(*) Looks exactly like the product image except that it's a shinier polish, so if you like the pictures you should like the look of the ring in person if you want a shiny ring
(*) Comfortable with very smooth surfaces everywhere

Cons:
(*) May inspire you to raise an orc army and try to take over the world...only to discover that orcs aren't nearly as effective against tanks as they are against swords. Oh, the humanity. Well, orcity...or whatever

column13: Sweet and simple pendant, treated turquoise -- the lady loved it!
column14:
My lovely lady loves to wear jewelry, and what's not to love? The shine, the sparkle, the glitz -- it also makes gift-giving very easy, knowing that if it glitters, she'll probably love it. She never takes it off, except when it comes to the beach or the pool, and then she only does it reluctantly and tells me the whole time how naked she feels because she doesn't have her necklaces on. When I saw this, I thought this was a perfect glittery budget-friendly alternative to wearing her good stuff when we're enjoying the chemical-filled pool and the abrasive sandy ocean. If it gets lost or ruined, no big deal, and she still can have the security of her shiny necklaces.

It arrived on a necklace card and wrapped in plastic so that it wouldn't be damaged in transit. The treated turquoise pendant is small but enough to make a statement and look elegant. When I gave it to her, she loved it (especially that it's teal, her favourite colour, and she thought I was ridiculously romantic for the gesture). She put it on right away and it has endured most of our summer adventures. The only drawbacks are when she wears it for extended periods of time and it leaves some discolouration and the chain is extremely short, making this necklace more like a choker -- but at least the chain can be replaced which we did after the first few times she wore it. Overall, we're both happy with what we got and I've been called The Best Boyfriend, so I win too!

I received this at a discount in exchange for a genuine critique.

column14:
This sterling silver and simulated diamond stacking rings was a gift for my sister in law who loves stacking rings. The best part is that these are 3 rings that can be worn together or separately. She loves wearing rings but is always afraid of losing precious rings while traveling as she has a habit of taking them off and has sometimes left rings behind. She was very pleased with these as they almost look like white gold and real diamond but she wouldn't be afraid of losing them any more.

These 3 rings have tiny diamonds set into the design and shine and sparkle. They are very well made and great enough special occasion wear but work just as well for every day wear.

This triplet ring was perfect for a gift as it came in a beautiful and heavy black ring box in a leather like finish with a gold embossed pattern. There was a white outer cardboard box to protect the ring box on the inside.

column6: BABEYOND Silver Art Deco Teardrop Evening Bridal Dangle Earrings Clear Cubic Zirconia Austrian Crystal
column14:
These earrings are so beautiful and shinny, yes the stones does have a lot of shine to them including the center big stone. The stones were very well studded and I could not find any one of them missing or misaligned, which are very commonly found in costume jewelry. One thing that I loved about the earrings are that, when ever I wear a dangling earring my ears starts to pain after a few minutes, but with this that did not happen. They are light weight which may be the reason I did not feel any pain wearing them for over 4-5 hours.
Being an Indian we wear a lot of Sari that are heavily embroidered and this earrings goes on very well with my Saris and other traditional dresses I wear. Wearing them to a party last night I got some cool compliments and my friends couldn't believe that it costs only $12, generally if you go to buy a costume jewelry like this in a store it will at least cost you $20 if not more.
The earrings came in a nice box ready to be gifted, so if you are planning on gifting them to someone, I am sure they will love it too.
**I received the product at a promotional offer in exchange of y unbiased and honest review.

column6: SmitCo LLC Toddler Jewelry, For Little Girls And Kids, Stretch Ladybug Necklace, Bracelet And Ring
column13: This Red and White Lady Bug Jewelry Set for Little Girls by SmitCo LLC is Absolutely Adorable!
column14:
This Red and White Lady Bug Jewelry Set for Little Girls by SmitCo LLC is Absolutely Adorable!
The Necklace features 2 Sections with Twelve 1/8" Red and White Wooden Beads each (one on either side of the Ladybug on the front of the necklace) and 1 section with Forty Five 1/8" Red and White Wooden Beads.
Each Section is Separated from the next by a 1" long by 3/4" wide Hand-Painted Wooden Ladybug. (3 Ladybugs Total).
The Ladybugs are painted both front and back, the fronts are detailed and the backs are a solid red color.
The Beads are Securely Strung onto a Sturdy Elastic Cord which offers a good amount of stretch, so the 5" x 4 1/2" un-stretched Necklace will easily go over a young child's head without breaking.
The Too Cute Matching Bracelet features Thirty 1/8" Red and White Wooden Beads and One 1" x 3/4" Ladybug.
Note: As the beads on this jewelry set are Small in Size, I would Not advise putting it on a child under the age of 3 without supervision, as they could cause a choking hazard should the child manage to accomplish the unlikely and break the elastic cord.
The entire set is shipped in a Very Attractive Shiny Gift Box.
This Ladybug Jewelry Set would be a welcomed gift by Any younger lady ages 3 and up.
I received mine at a promotional price in exchange for testing and review and am gifting it to my 5 yr old niece. I have no doubt that my sister in law will have a difficult time getting her to take it off once she puts it on!
A+++ Recommendation!

column6: 10k Gold Earrings with Heart Cutouts
column13: Beautiful earrings; picture on Amazon does not do them justice.
column14:
I saw the Cut Out Hearts Earrings on Vine and they looked beautiful. I ordered them and am now delighted to say that these earrings are more lovely to look at when my wife is wearing them than what can be seen in the pictures on Amazon. The pictures don't do them justice. My wife is delighted with them.

One picture shown on Amazon gives us a woman in profile wearing the earrings. This picture makes the earrings look much smaller than what they are when worn by my wife. These earrings are what I would call mid-size; they are not too large or small, but just right, in my opinion.

The shape of the earrings is a tear drop and the inside of the tear drop has gold hearts strung from top to bottom. The clasp is large; my wife had them attached to her ears in a few moments.

I have saved the best for last. The first thing my wife said when she saw these earrings is \\\Look how they sparkle.\\\\\" That comes across a little bit in the picture on Amazon, but in person the sparkle defines these earrings. Beautiful!

If anyone reading this review decides to buy these earrings, please come back to this review and tell me if you like them as much as I do. Thanks."
